1
00:00:14,014 --> 00:00:16,116
PREVIOUSLY

2
00:00:16,182 --> 00:00:20,053
The ladies Gen Z look up to,
Jang Won-young and Lee Eun-ji!

3
00:00:20,120 --> 00:00:21,421
AND NEW CHALLENGING CHEFS!

4
00:00:21,488 --> 00:00:24,591
A star Chinese chef, Jung Ji-sun!

5
00:00:25,658 --> 00:00:28,895
<i>The first and only chef in Korea</i>
<i>who has two one-star Michelin restaurants.</i>

6
00:00:28,962 --> 00:00:30,230
Chef Son Jong-won!

7
00:00:30,296 --> 00:00:32,165
-Chef Son Jong-won.
-It's great to have you.

8
00:00:32,999 --> 00:00:34,834
Chef Hyun-suk

9
00:00:34,901 --> 00:00:38,171
and the new show-off chef, Chef Sung-jun.

10
00:00:38,238 --> 00:00:40,440
It's the Show-off Chef cook-off.

11
00:00:40,507 --> 00:00:41,674
Mmm!

12
00:00:41,741 --> 00:00:43,643
SHE MAKES DOLPHIN SOUNDS
WHEN THE FOOD IS DELICIOUS

13
00:00:43,710 --> 00:00:45,879
Who's the winner?

14
00:00:45,945 --> 00:00:47,280
It was Choi Hyun-suk.

15
00:00:47,347 --> 00:00:50,550
I like dishes that are like
at fine dining restaurants.

16
00:00:50,617 --> 00:00:52,452
<i>I'll make Jang-chelin Course Meal.</i>

17
00:00:52,519 --> 00:00:55,588
I want to use the pistachio spread
and prepare endive salad.

18
00:00:55,655 --> 00:00:58,058
Then I wanted to make rib eye steak
as well as Brussels sprouts.

19
00:00:58,124 --> 00:01:01,461
Lastly, I'll use macadamia nuts
and make ice cream.

20
00:01:01,528 --> 00:01:03,463
Won-young's Course Meal.

21
00:01:03,530 --> 00:01:05,732
I'll use red as a theme.

22
00:01:05,799 --> 00:01:08,601
I prepared some beet as an appetizer.

23
00:01:08,668 --> 00:01:10,970
You said you liked chuck flap tail,
so I'll grill that lightly.

24
00:01:11,037 --> 00:01:13,073
I also prepared dessert with strawberries.

25
00:01:14,574 --> 00:01:15,775
FINISHED THE DESSERT

26
00:01:16,309 --> 00:01:17,310
FINISHED THE APPETIZER

27
00:01:17,377 --> 00:01:19,712
He's done with two dishes.

28
00:01:19,779 --> 00:01:22,115
-Are you done?
-I'm done.

29
00:01:22,182 --> 00:01:23,683
Chef Sam is done!

30
00:01:24,451 --> 00:01:26,453
BUT SON JONG-WON
HASN'T FINISHED ANYTHING

31
00:01:26,519 --> 00:01:28,488
Chef Sam finishes first.

32
00:01:28,555 --> 00:01:30,957
You have 45 seconds. Stay calm.

33
00:01:31,958 --> 00:01:33,426
HE EVEN STARTED 1 MINUTE EARLIER

34
00:01:33,493 --> 00:01:34,828
Hurry up.

35
00:01:34,894 --> 00:01:36,996
-He has 30 seconds.
-It's 35 seconds!

36
00:01:37,063 --> 00:01:38,198
He seems relaxed, though.

37
00:01:38,264 --> 00:01:40,233
-He's using tweezers.
-Tweezers!

38
00:01:40,300 --> 00:01:41,701
Tweezers!

39
00:01:41,768 --> 00:01:43,503
Do you have hand tremors?

40
00:01:43,570 --> 00:01:45,371
His hands are trembling.

41
00:01:47,373 --> 00:01:51,411
THE LAST LEAF
OF JANG-CHELIN COURSE MEAL

42
00:01:51,478 --> 00:01:54,647
Now, 20 seconds.
Eun-ji, any last words of support?

43
00:01:54,714 --> 00:01:56,015
I love you!

44
00:01:56,082 --> 00:01:57,083
OH, MY

45
00:01:57,150 --> 00:01:58,418
I LOVE YOU!!!!!

46
00:02:00,019 --> 00:02:02,055
HE FINISHES EVERYTHING
METICULOUSLY

47
00:02:02,122 --> 00:02:05,358
And now, ten seconds.

48
00:02:05,425 --> 00:02:09,662
SON JONG-WON SAFELY FINISHES
THE COURSE MEAL TOO

49
00:02:10,597 --> 00:02:13,133
It didn't take all of the 15 minutes.

50
00:02:13,967 --> 00:02:16,736
-They look great.
-These look so pretty.

51
00:02:16,803 --> 00:02:19,439
-How did they do this in 15 minutes?
-They're so pretty.

52
00:02:19,506 --> 00:02:24,277
The dishes for Won-young were
all finished.

53
00:02:24,344 --> 00:02:27,947
You said you wanted a classy dish,
and that how it looked was important.

54
00:02:28,014 --> 00:02:31,151
Which do you prefer visually?

55
00:02:31,217 --> 00:02:34,921
First… Did you choose the plates yourself?

56
00:02:34,988 --> 00:02:36,589
-The plates? Yes.
-Did you do it?

57
00:02:36,656 --> 00:02:38,124
-Did you pick these?
-Yes.

58
00:02:39,192 --> 00:02:40,193
So detailed.

59
00:02:40,260 --> 00:02:46,032
Chef Jong-won's plates
and the overall presentation is my type.

60
00:02:46,099 --> 00:02:47,867
-Something fancier.
-You prefer something fancier.

61
00:02:47,934 --> 00:02:49,369
-You're right.
-That's right.

62
00:02:49,435 --> 00:02:53,139
Now, please have a taste
of Chef Sam's Won-young's Course Meal.

63
00:02:53,206 --> 00:02:55,408
MAIN DISH: GRILLED CHUCK FLAP
WITH APPLE DOENJANG SAUCE

64
00:02:56,109 --> 00:02:58,478
How did they make 3 dishes in 15 minutes?

65
00:02:58,545 --> 00:03:02,182
Gosh, these are so beautiful
even at the second look.

66
00:03:02,248 --> 00:03:05,552
CHEF SAM'S WON-YOUNG'S COURSE MEAL

67
00:03:05,618 --> 00:03:06,653
The beets first.

68
00:03:06,719 --> 00:03:08,621
I see. Just like that.

69
00:03:09,289 --> 00:03:11,558
-The colors look beautiful.
-This is so pretty!

70
00:03:12,058 --> 00:03:15,361
AND GORGEOUS WON-YOUNG

71
00:03:15,428 --> 00:03:19,165
-The red and the green.
-They go well together.

72
00:03:19,232 --> 00:03:22,535
She has the charms to
make people stop in their tracks.

73
00:03:22,602 --> 00:03:24,871
-Hmm?
-Yes?

74
00:03:24,938 --> 00:03:27,740
She sounds like a curious dolphin.

75
00:03:27,807 --> 00:03:30,610
-How do you make a taste like this?
-I see.

76
00:03:30,677 --> 00:03:33,213
-The beet?
-In a good sense or a bad sense?

77
00:03:33,279 --> 00:03:36,516
-I meant that 1,000% good.
-It was 1,000% good.

78
00:03:36,583 --> 00:03:38,651
"How do you make a taste like this?"

79
00:03:38,718 --> 00:03:41,321
What did you use for the sauce?

80
00:03:41,387 --> 00:03:44,557
Camembert cheese works
as perfect seasoning when it's melted.

81
00:03:44,624 --> 00:03:46,025
<i>I just melted it with milk.</i>

82
00:03:46,092 --> 00:03:48,161
<i>-You said you liked milk.</i>
<i>-With milk.</i>

83
00:03:48,228 --> 00:03:50,129
It was a perfect match.

84
00:03:50,196 --> 00:03:51,698
A PERFECT MATCH
FOR WON-YOUNG'S PALATE

85
00:03:51,764 --> 00:03:53,600
-After all, it's Won-young's Course Meal.
-Yes.

86
00:03:53,666 --> 00:03:56,836
I said I wanted to eat my food
with my eyes first, then my mouth.

87
00:03:56,903 --> 00:03:59,138
-And this dish passes that test.
-It passed.

88
00:03:59,205 --> 00:04:00,573
-The appetizer passes.
-Yes.

89
00:04:00,640 --> 00:04:01,841
Onto the main dish.

90
00:04:01,908 --> 00:04:04,110
THE MAIN DISH IS GRILLED CHUCK FLAP
WITH APPLE DOENJANG SAUCE

91
00:04:04,177 --> 00:04:06,346
-It looks so good.
-That looks so amazing.

92
00:04:06,412 --> 00:04:09,515
-What's this?
-That's meat with blended arugula.

93
00:04:09,582 --> 00:04:11,417
I wanted her to try that
instead of wasabi.

94
00:04:11,484 --> 00:04:13,853
Gosh, the arugula paste.

95
00:04:13,920 --> 00:04:16,689
She can eat the meat with that paste

96
00:04:16,756 --> 00:04:19,325
and the apple sauce underneath.

97
00:04:24,430 --> 00:04:25,465
MMM

98
00:04:26,799 --> 00:04:30,103
I've had all kinds of beef cuts

99
00:04:30,169 --> 00:04:32,205
-from a variety of places.
-I see.

100
00:04:32,272 --> 00:04:36,442
But I've never had beef with apple sauce

101
00:04:36,509 --> 00:04:39,879
and arugula paste in any of them.

102
00:04:39,946 --> 00:04:40,980
They go so well together.

103
00:04:41,047 --> 00:04:43,082
-I see.
-They go so well together.

104
00:04:43,149 --> 00:04:44,417
The mix must work very well.

105
00:04:44,484 --> 00:04:47,120
You said you used doenjang, right?

106
00:04:47,186 --> 00:04:50,957
This tastes like a Korean fusion dish,
including the plate.

107
00:04:51,024 --> 00:04:52,592
It looks like a roof tile.

108
00:04:52,659 --> 00:04:55,928
A roof tile?

109
00:04:55,995 --> 00:04:58,431
-Lastly, the dessert.
-Lastly, it's the dessert.

110
00:04:58,498 --> 00:05:00,166
He had used egg yolks.

111
00:05:00,233 --> 00:05:01,234
HOW WILL JANG-CHELIN RESPOND?

112
00:05:01,301 --> 00:05:04,137
-She tries the zabaione first.
-Zabaione.

113
00:05:04,203 --> 00:05:06,072
-Hmm?
-Yes?

114
00:05:06,139 --> 00:05:08,308
Why does it taste
like vanilla custard cream?

115
00:05:08,374 --> 00:05:11,377
-You said you liked macadamia ice cream.
-The ice cream.

116
00:05:11,444 --> 00:05:12,879
I mixed it with egg yolks.

117
00:05:12,945 --> 00:05:15,381
-I see. And the strawberries.
-With the vanilla ice cream.

118
00:05:15,448 --> 00:05:17,083
HOW DOES STRAWBERRY
WORK WITH ZABAIONE?

119
00:05:17,150 --> 00:05:18,618
-Mmm.
-So?

120
00:05:22,789 --> 00:05:24,390
Wasn't that the first time?

121
00:05:24,457 --> 00:05:27,160
-She gave thumbs up for the first time.
-It's the first time.

122
00:05:27,226 --> 00:05:31,331
When I had these together,
the macadamia nuts come strong in the end.

123
00:05:31,397 --> 00:05:34,400
-It's very savory and nutty.
-Even though it was so little.

124
00:05:34,467 --> 00:05:35,868
It's really good.

125
00:05:36,969 --> 00:05:41,641
Next, Chef Jong-won's
Jang-chelin Course Meal.

126
00:05:41,708 --> 00:05:44,277
A HARMONY OF FRIED BRUSSELS SPROUTS
AND RIB EYE STEAK

127
00:05:44,844 --> 00:05:45,845
AND MACADAMIA ICE CREAM

128
00:05:45,912 --> 00:05:47,480
SERVED WITH GOAT CHEESE
AND CHESTNUT JAM

129
00:05:47,547 --> 00:05:51,584
CHEF SON JONG-WON'S
JANG-CHELIN COURSE MEAL

130
00:05:51,651 --> 00:05:54,053
Let me try a bite of this.

131
00:05:54,120 --> 00:05:57,190
-So this is pistachio and endive?
-This one.

132
00:05:57,757 --> 00:05:59,425
-It looks so good.
-This one.

133
00:05:59,492 --> 00:06:01,461
-That one looks good.
-He had a tough time with it.

134
00:06:01,527 --> 00:06:03,863
He made it small enough for her to eat.

135
00:06:03,930 --> 00:06:07,400
How will it taste
after she has everything together?

136
00:06:07,900 --> 00:06:10,169
It tastes like this.

137
00:06:10,236 --> 00:06:11,571
Stop giving him hearts!

138
00:06:12,905 --> 00:06:14,073
EUN-JI'S CRACKDOWN

139
00:06:14,140 --> 00:06:15,475
Stop giving him hearts, Won-young!

140
00:06:15,541 --> 00:06:19,345
-This makes me give hearts.
-It makes her give hearts.

141
00:06:19,412 --> 00:06:22,281
The thumbs up
and the hearts must taste different.

142
00:06:22,348 --> 00:06:24,784
The order was actually,
"Hold your breath, love dining."

143
00:06:24,851 --> 00:06:26,919
You're right.

144
00:06:26,986 --> 00:06:28,788
Will she pick Chef Jong-won?

145
00:06:28,855 --> 00:06:31,224
-The chances seem high.
-It does seem like it.

146
00:06:31,290 --> 00:06:33,359
THE JANG-CHELIN MATCH, APPETIZERS:
SON JONG-WON OVER SAM KIM

147
00:06:33,426 --> 00:06:34,727
-The main dish.
-Yes.

148
00:06:34,794 --> 00:06:38,998
-I want to try the Brussels sprouts first.
-Yes, the Brussels sprouts.

149
00:06:39,065 --> 00:06:40,767
It apparently tasted a bit burnt.

150
00:06:40,833 --> 00:06:42,969
These look burnt.

151
00:06:43,035 --> 00:06:44,637
It's burnt, but why is it delicious?

152
00:06:44,704 --> 00:06:46,773
-I see. It's good?
-It's burnt yet tasty.

153
00:06:48,508 --> 00:06:49,942
First, the Brussels sprouts.

154
00:06:50,009 --> 00:06:51,744
Mmm. Hmm?

155
00:06:51,811 --> 00:06:54,480
It tastes burnt, but it seems intentional.

156
00:06:54,547 --> 00:06:55,915
-Intentionally burnt.
-Intentionally burnt.

157
00:06:55,982 --> 00:06:57,283
Let me ask to make it official.

158
00:06:57,350 --> 00:06:59,986
Was it supposed to be burnt a little?

159
00:07:00,052 --> 00:07:02,188
I caused a lot of Maillard reaction
on the outside

160
00:07:02,255 --> 00:07:05,091
to make it crunchy
as the inside got cooked.

161
00:07:05,158 --> 00:07:08,694
-The crunchiness was intentional.
-The inside cooks as it becomes crunchy.

162
00:07:08,761 --> 00:07:11,931
I'd complain right away
if he served it to someone like me.

163
00:07:12,799 --> 00:07:13,800
"Why is this burnt?"

164
00:07:13,866 --> 00:07:16,335
"Are you telling me
to eat this burnt food?"

165
00:07:16,402 --> 00:07:17,804
-Those old men.
-Yes.

166
00:07:17,870 --> 00:07:20,006
-How's the meat?
-The meat.

167
00:07:20,072 --> 00:07:21,874
Mmm.

168
00:07:21,941 --> 00:07:23,176
Is it because of the cut?

169
00:07:23,242 --> 00:07:26,145
-I preferred Chef Sam's meat.
-She prefers Chef Sam's meat.

170
00:07:26,212 --> 00:07:28,247
I preferred Chef Sam's meat.

171
00:07:28,314 --> 00:07:30,450
She prefers Chef Sam's meat.

172
00:07:30,516 --> 00:07:32,218
She evaluates these right on the spot.

173
00:07:32,285 --> 00:07:33,286
We don't know yet.

174
00:07:33,352 --> 00:07:35,488
-It's not over until it is.
-Right.

175
00:07:35,555 --> 00:07:36,756
-Now, the dessert.
-The dessert.

176
00:07:36,823 --> 00:07:39,225
-Lastly, the dessert.
-The dessert.

177
00:07:40,259 --> 00:07:41,627
-My gosh.
-What?

178
00:07:41,694 --> 00:07:43,496
The cheese broke like a shell.

179
00:07:43,563 --> 00:07:44,897
-A shell?
-It's like

180
00:07:44,964 --> 00:07:49,936
crème brûlée or frozen chocolate.
You know, how it breaks when it's hard.

181
00:07:50,002 --> 00:07:51,671
Like how they're split.

182
00:07:51,737 --> 00:07:53,873
-I saw him add chestnut jam too.
-Goat cheese.

183
00:07:53,940 --> 00:07:55,475
Please try it
with the chestnut jam inside.

184
00:07:55,541 --> 00:07:57,510
Right? I saw you using chestnut jam.

185
00:07:57,577 --> 00:08:00,046
-That looks really good.
-It looks good.

186
00:08:00,112 --> 00:08:01,380
-Mmm.
-Oh?

187
00:08:02,682 --> 00:08:04,383
-How is it?
-Was it this or this?

188
00:08:04,450 --> 00:08:06,986
HERE COMES THE HEARTS

189
00:08:07,553 --> 00:08:09,255
DIFFERENT REACTIONS TO HER HEARTS

190
00:08:09,322 --> 00:08:12,959
I've never had goat cheese with ice cream,
but this was really good.

191
00:08:13,025 --> 00:08:15,695
You said his dessert was good too.

192
00:08:15,761 --> 00:08:19,298
But these two came
in completely different styles.

193
00:08:19,365 --> 00:08:22,335
-I need to consider this real hard.
-You're right.

194
00:08:22,401 --> 00:08:24,737
-It's harder if they're different.
-She'll think now.

195
00:08:24,804 --> 00:08:28,608
-Thank you for your hard work, chefs.
-Yes.

196
00:08:29,542 --> 00:08:30,910
I'm not sure who'll win.

197
00:08:30,977 --> 00:08:33,913
<i>Hold your breath, love dining</i>

198
00:08:33,980 --> 00:08:37,250
That was a match
between two Western cuisine masters.

199
00:08:37,316 --> 00:08:39,285
Will it be Sam Kim, the original chef?

200
00:08:39,352 --> 00:08:41,954
-Or Son Jong-won, who had his debut round?
-Who will it be?

201
00:08:42,021 --> 00:08:44,657
-Who will Won-young choose?
-Who is it?

202
00:08:44,724 --> 00:08:46,225
Let's find out. Show us!

203
00:08:46,292 --> 00:08:47,860
Who won?

204
00:08:47,927 --> 00:08:50,796
-I want to know.
-Who'll get the star?

205
00:08:50,863 --> 00:08:52,832
SON JONG-WON WINS

206
00:08:53,399 --> 00:08:55,034
CHEF SON JONG-WON'S
JANG-CHELIN COURSE MEAL WINS

207
00:08:55,101 --> 00:08:56,102
It was Son Jong-won!

208
00:08:56,168 --> 00:08:58,004
HE WINS AGAINST SAM KIM
AND GETS HIS FIRST STAR

209
00:08:58,070 --> 00:08:59,438
Son Jong-won wins against Sam Kim!

210
00:09:00,239 --> 00:09:02,475
My gosh. I can't believe this.

211
00:09:02,542 --> 00:09:04,944
Chef Jong-won just had his debut round

212
00:09:05,011 --> 00:09:07,713
and won against Chef Sam,
the experienced returning chef.

213
00:09:08,281 --> 00:09:11,984
This was quite unexpected
at the beginning of this season.

214
00:09:12,051 --> 00:09:14,120
-What a shame.
-Why did you pick him?

215
00:09:14,186 --> 00:09:19,425
This plate had already captured my heart
from the start with this appetizer.

216
00:09:19,492 --> 00:09:23,229
I thought this was something
only Chef Jong-won could do.

217
00:09:23,296 --> 00:09:26,799
-The dessert had extraordinary details.
-I see.

218
00:09:26,866 --> 00:09:29,535
I wanted to use these good ingredients

219
00:09:29,602 --> 00:09:32,371
and put in my good heart,
hoping you'd take a rest.

220
00:09:32,438 --> 00:09:34,340
I felt that in his presentation.

221
00:09:34,407 --> 00:09:36,909
It's almost impossible

222
00:09:36,976 --> 00:09:40,146
to recreate a fine dining experience
in just 15 minutes.

223
00:09:40,212 --> 00:09:44,584
But I could see how serious they were
to meet my demand.

224
00:09:44,650 --> 00:09:46,752
I want to thank you both.

225
00:09:46,819 --> 00:09:47,887
It was so hard to pick.

226
00:09:47,954 --> 00:09:49,889
-This means…
-Thank you.

227
00:09:49,956 --> 00:09:53,259
-Chef Jong-won wins his debut round.
-Congratulations.

228
00:09:53,326 --> 00:09:54,727
Congratulations on your first star!

229
00:09:54,794 --> 00:09:56,329
The star chef surely is different.

230
00:09:56,395 --> 00:09:58,331
-He is different.
-The star is different.

231
00:09:58,397 --> 00:10:00,099
Gosh, double stars.

232
00:10:00,166 --> 00:10:02,802
SAM KIM CLEANS THE KITCHEN
AFTER THE FIERCE COMPETITION

233
00:10:02,868 --> 00:10:05,371
Let me clean up the food waste.

234
00:10:05,438 --> 00:10:07,239
I can even move it like this.

235
00:10:08,307 --> 00:10:10,676
EASY TO OPEN
WITH A WAVE OF THE HAND

236
00:10:15,147 --> 00:10:18,851
Let's see. I can control this
even when I'm outside?

237
00:10:18,918 --> 00:10:20,186
That's really convenient.

238
00:10:20,252 --> 00:10:21,921
EASY TO CONTROL THE SETTINGS
WHEREVER YOU ARE

239
00:10:21,988 --> 00:10:24,290
MEAT

240
00:10:24,357 --> 00:10:27,193
A FEW HOURS LATER,
THE FOOD WASTE TURNED INTO DIRT

241
00:10:27,259 --> 00:10:31,297
We're here with Won-young and Eun-ji,
the ladies Gen Z look up to.

242
00:10:31,364 --> 00:10:34,467
Eun-ji, I heard
you tossed and turned all night.

243
00:10:34,533 --> 00:10:36,636
I was really excited for this.

244
00:10:36,702 --> 00:10:40,706
Because <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>
first went on air in 2014,

245
00:10:40,773 --> 00:10:43,542
-and I also debuted in 2014.
-That's the timeline.

246
00:10:43,609 --> 00:10:46,379
Back then, I was a rookie,

247
00:10:46,445 --> 00:10:50,282
and this show only had
the biggest stars and celebrities.

248
00:10:50,349 --> 00:10:52,652
But I watched it
alone at home over a drink.

249
00:10:52,718 --> 00:10:56,589
It took me 11 years to be here.

250
00:10:56,656 --> 00:10:59,291
-It's really such an honor.
-Oh, my.

251
00:10:59,358 --> 00:11:02,194
I see. You probably faced
many hardships right after debuting.

252
00:11:02,261 --> 00:11:04,997
Yes, I didn't have
much pocket money to spend.

253
00:11:05,064 --> 00:11:06,999
So I took up jobs at a kids cafe and such

254
00:11:07,066 --> 00:11:09,535
and worked two jobs throughout that time.

255
00:11:09,602 --> 00:11:13,105
I heard she was very popular
at her workplace too.

256
00:11:13,172 --> 00:11:15,207
I was really good with kids

257
00:11:15,274 --> 00:11:17,443
that I even got tipped at the kids cafe.

258
00:11:18,144 --> 00:11:19,145
HOW GOOD WAS SHE WITH THEM?

259
00:11:19,211 --> 00:11:20,913
-Because you were so good with them?
-Yes.

260
00:11:20,980 --> 00:11:23,215
Kids love secrets, right?

261
00:11:23,282 --> 00:11:24,316
I'd go over and say,

262
00:11:24,383 --> 00:11:27,520
"Do you want to know a secret?"

263
00:11:27,586 --> 00:11:30,489
Then they'd all get focused
instead of getting noisy.

264
00:11:30,556 --> 00:11:32,191
I'd play with them like that.

265
00:11:32,258 --> 00:11:34,260
I'd put a doll in my stomach and go,

266
00:11:34,326 --> 00:11:36,228
"I'm about to have a baby!"

267
00:11:36,295 --> 00:11:38,097
EXCELLENT PERFORMANCE

268
00:11:38,164 --> 00:11:41,467
-They'd operate on me and stuff. Really.
-Oh, gosh.

269
00:11:41,534 --> 00:11:43,836
-Why don't you share a secret…
-She's really good.

270
00:11:43,903 --> 00:11:45,871
with Chef Kang-rok as well?

271
00:11:45,938 --> 00:11:49,575
-I'll tell you a secret after the shoot.
-He'll like that.

272
00:11:49,642 --> 00:11:50,710
I'M CURIOUS

273
00:11:50,776 --> 00:11:52,611
Those days have come together

274
00:11:52,678 --> 00:11:55,081
to make Eun-ji who she is today.

275
00:11:55,147 --> 00:11:59,685
Won-young, have you always dreamed
of becoming a singer? Anything else?

276
00:11:59,752 --> 00:12:03,322
Actually, I always wrote down
something else as my dream

277
00:12:03,389 --> 00:12:04,790
since my elementary school days.

278
00:12:04,857 --> 00:12:07,059
-I wanted to be an announcer.
-That suits you.

279
00:12:07,126 --> 00:12:09,729
-It does suit her.
-It suits her perfectly.

280
00:12:09,795 --> 00:12:11,130
Hello.

281
00:12:12,131 --> 00:12:14,433
Do you want to say something

282
00:12:14,500 --> 00:12:16,001
-as an announcer?
-What can I say?

283
00:12:16,068 --> 00:12:17,903
I'm the newsreader. Let's begin.

284
00:12:17,970 --> 00:12:21,107
<i>Chef & My Fridge</i> recently became
the biggest issue.

285
00:12:21,173 --> 00:12:23,375
Let's hear it from the scene.
Announcer Jang Won-young!

286
00:12:24,043 --> 00:12:25,044
Yes, hello.

287
00:12:25,111 --> 00:12:27,113
I am Jang Won-young,
reporting from the scene.

288
00:12:27,179 --> 00:12:30,883
I'm here
with eight prestigious chefs right now.

289
00:12:30,950 --> 00:12:33,519
There's a keen interest
on the various wonderful dishes

290
00:12:33,586 --> 00:12:35,287
they're about to make today.

291
00:12:35,354 --> 00:12:36,956
She's good.

292
00:12:37,022 --> 00:12:38,023
SHE'S SO GOOD

293
00:12:38,090 --> 00:12:40,092
Reporting from the scene,
Announcer Jang Won-young.

294
00:12:40,159 --> 00:12:41,894
-Oh, my.
-I see.

295
00:12:41,961 --> 00:12:44,897
-She uses an unlikely word like "keen."
-"Keen."

296
00:12:44,964 --> 00:12:46,966
-Reporter Lee Eun-ji?
-Yes!

297
00:12:47,032 --> 00:12:49,268
Oh, my. Look where I am today.

298
00:12:49,335 --> 00:12:51,036
I'm here at <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>.

299
00:12:51,103 --> 00:12:52,538
It's me, Park Soo-rim.

300
00:12:54,440 --> 00:12:57,543
One of her most renowned predecessors
was Park Soo-rim.

301
00:12:57,610 --> 00:13:00,479
-She made history.
-Yes, it's the <i>Love on the Air</i> style.

302
00:13:00,546 --> 00:13:02,047
THAT WAS FUNNY

303
00:13:02,114 --> 00:13:03,415
I'm here with someone today.

304
00:13:03,482 --> 00:13:06,118
Now, is this person

305
00:13:07,720 --> 00:13:10,723
the first love or not?

306
00:13:10,790 --> 00:13:11,824
Let's find out!

307
00:13:17,263 --> 00:13:18,430
Let's find out!

308
00:13:18,497 --> 00:13:19,765
BLINK

309
00:13:19,832 --> 00:13:21,634
-Are you sulking?
-No.

310
00:13:22,234 --> 00:13:23,235
KANG-ROK IS HAVING REAL FUN

311
00:13:23,302 --> 00:13:25,104
-She's good.
-Kang-rok.

312
00:13:25,171 --> 00:13:26,338
Don't be sulky.

313
00:13:26,405 --> 00:13:29,308
She's putting him
in the biggest spot today.

314
00:13:29,375 --> 00:13:31,844
-Don't be sulky.
-Will he cook all right today?

315
00:13:31,911 --> 00:13:34,079
-He may get sick at home.
-It may happen.

316
00:13:34,146 --> 00:13:37,550
I won't talk to you
for the next 20 minutes.

317
00:13:37,616 --> 00:13:40,820
While they play the round
to make Eun-ji's orders,

318
00:13:40,886 --> 00:13:43,222
why don't you try
and do the five-minute check?

319
00:13:43,289 --> 00:13:45,591
I want to try.
I often saw what you did out there.

320
00:13:45,658 --> 00:13:48,227
You tend to tease them a little.

321
00:13:48,294 --> 00:13:50,796
-You're right.
-We didn't tease them.

322
00:13:50,863 --> 00:13:52,331
We're serious.

323
00:13:52,398 --> 00:13:55,201
-You made them confused on purpose.
-She picked up the worst from us.

324
00:13:55,267 --> 00:13:57,903
We'll go,
"How are things out there, Won-young?"

325
00:13:57,970 --> 00:14:00,372
-Then you can tell us.
-It's too salty!

326
00:14:00,439 --> 00:14:03,375
-Do something honest like that.
-She's good.

327
00:14:03,442 --> 00:14:08,380
Please look forward to seeing
how Won-young will do on the scene.

328
00:14:08,447 --> 00:14:11,884
As always, let's do this
before we open the fridge.

329
00:14:11,951 --> 00:14:14,220
We'll decide on the contenders.

330
00:14:14,286 --> 00:14:15,588
Lee Yeon-bok and Kim Poong

331
00:14:15,654 --> 00:14:18,791
against the new chefs,
Choi Kang-rok and Jung Ji-sun. The four.

332
00:14:18,858 --> 00:14:22,061
What are the orders Eun-ji made today?

333
00:14:22,127 --> 00:14:25,097
Let's find out what her order is.
Let's see it.

334
00:14:25,164 --> 00:14:27,933
-Yes.
-Here are Eun-ji's orders.

335
00:14:29,602 --> 00:14:31,971
Hello, it's me. Any bar snacks there?

336
00:14:32,037 --> 00:14:35,074
<i>Hello, it's me</i>

337
00:14:35,140 --> 00:14:38,444
<i>Any bar snacks there?</i>

338
00:14:38,510 --> 00:14:40,446
-Snacks with drinks?
-Yes.

339
00:14:40,512 --> 00:14:42,548
-You drink alone often.
-I love to.

340
00:14:42,615 --> 00:14:44,850
I wanted something to eat with a drink.

341
00:14:44,917 --> 00:14:49,955
I thought it'd be nice
if it were a simple dish I could make

342
00:14:50,022 --> 00:14:52,958
when I drink alone
after showering at home.

343
00:14:53,025 --> 00:14:54,460
What do you usually drink?

344
00:14:54,526 --> 00:14:56,395
-I mostly drink soju.
-Soju.

345
00:14:56,462 --> 00:14:57,630
Not soju, but so-ju.

346
00:14:57,696 --> 00:14:59,098
-Is it different from soju?
-No.

347
00:14:59,164 --> 00:15:01,066
It sounds more delicious
when I say it like that.

348
00:15:02,034 --> 00:15:03,202
So-ju.

349
00:15:03,269 --> 00:15:06,372
And here's the second order.

350
00:15:06,438 --> 00:15:09,108
Eun-ji's order is
"Satisfying leftover delivery food."

351
00:15:09,174 --> 00:15:11,110
I mostly order food at home,

352
00:15:11,176 --> 00:15:13,445
and the portion is bigger
than what I can eat.

353
00:15:13,512 --> 00:15:15,381
So, in the end,

354
00:15:15,447 --> 00:15:18,584
I always end up freezing the leftovers.

355
00:15:18,651 --> 00:15:24,523
So I wanted to eat something I can make
with the leftover delivery food.

356
00:15:24,590 --> 00:15:27,459
-I see. It's a shame to throw it out.
-Yes, it is.

357
00:15:27,526 --> 00:15:30,863
<i>Hello, it's me</i>

358
00:15:30,930 --> 00:15:32,831
<i>Any bar snacks there?</i>

359
00:15:32,898 --> 00:15:34,833
She's calling on Kang-rok.

360
00:15:34,900 --> 00:15:39,872
<i>Hello, why won't you say anything?</i>

361
00:15:39,939 --> 00:15:42,141
It's time to make your choice.
Which will it be?

362
00:15:42,207 --> 00:15:44,410
THE INTROVERT
GETS PICKED BY THE EXTROVERT

363
00:15:44,476 --> 00:15:47,846
-She wants you to choose one.
-She likes so-ju.

364
00:15:47,913 --> 00:15:50,182
-I'll do that.
-Kang-rok chooses that.

365
00:15:50,249 --> 00:15:53,352
-She almost forced him to do this.
-The bar snack.

366
00:15:53,419 --> 00:15:55,120
Only one spot remains,

367
00:15:55,187 --> 00:15:57,790
so naturally, Chef Ji-sun will take
satisfying leftover delivery food.

368
00:15:57,856 --> 00:16:00,592
We're left
with Lee Yeon-bok and Kim Poong.

369
00:16:00,659 --> 00:16:01,927
-This will be fun.
-The two.

370
00:16:01,994 --> 00:16:04,396
The order I can meet the best is

371
00:16:04,463 --> 00:16:06,999
satisfying leftover delivery food.

372
00:16:07,066 --> 00:16:09,134
You're going up against Chef Ji-sun?

373
00:16:09,201 --> 00:16:12,471
Poong chooses
satisfying leftover delivery food,

374
00:16:12,538 --> 00:16:14,340
so Chef Yeon-bok

375
00:16:14,406 --> 00:16:16,809
will make a bar snack
against Chef Kang-rok.

376
00:16:16,875 --> 00:16:20,646
Let's find out
what Eun-ji has in her fridge.

377
00:16:20,713 --> 00:16:22,915
The contenders should take a good look.

378
00:16:23,515 --> 00:16:25,017
Did you pull it out from home?

379
00:16:25,084 --> 00:16:26,885
It looks so real.

380
00:16:26,952 --> 00:16:29,488
I had zero interest in cooking,

381
00:16:29,555 --> 00:16:31,090
so I didn't think I'd cook a lot.

382
00:16:31,156 --> 00:16:34,059
That was why I chose
a tiny fridge like that.

383
00:16:34,126 --> 00:16:35,594
But you keep it at home, right?

384
00:16:37,029 --> 00:16:40,232
<i>-Yes, it's next to my kitchen.</i>
<i>-Yes, I see.</i>

385
00:16:40,299 --> 00:16:43,235
I was too busy at the end of the year,

386
00:16:43,302 --> 00:16:45,204
so I haven't cleaned it out at all.

387
00:16:45,270 --> 00:16:46,772
I'm really scared right now.

388
00:16:46,839 --> 00:16:48,741
I wonder what you have in there.

389
00:16:49,308 --> 00:16:51,343
Something might be alive.

390
00:16:51,410 --> 00:16:54,113
"Something might be alive"?

391
00:16:54,179 --> 00:16:56,482
-No way.
-I see.

392
00:16:56,548 --> 00:16:59,852
We present Eun-ji's fridge!

393
00:17:00,419 --> 00:17:02,221
THE CHEFS ARE IN SHOCK

394
00:17:03,188 --> 00:17:05,557
Whoa, what was that?

395
00:17:05,624 --> 00:17:06,792
That was a surprise.

396
00:17:06,859 --> 00:17:08,660
Just get a bigger fridge!

397
00:17:08,727 --> 00:17:11,230
-It's about to burst.
-What is this?

398
00:17:11,296 --> 00:17:13,399
-Something fell out.
-A pack of arugula fell out.

399
00:17:13,465 --> 00:17:15,067
-Arugula. What?
-Has it gone bad?

400
00:17:15,134 --> 00:17:17,770
This was packed
back on December 12th, 2024.

401
00:17:17,836 --> 00:17:19,805
It already became fertilizer.

402
00:17:20,572 --> 00:17:22,474
-That's…
-That's not going to work.

403
00:17:22,541 --> 00:17:25,644
I just like to pour olive oil
over some salad veggies

404
00:17:25,711 --> 00:17:27,946
-and season it with salt and pepper.
-I see.

405
00:17:28,013 --> 00:17:29,615
I was going to eat it, then I forgot.

406
00:17:29,681 --> 00:17:30,949
-I see.
-Don't smell it.

407
00:17:31,016 --> 00:17:33,452
Spoiled veggies are the most likely
to give you food poisoning,

408
00:17:33,519 --> 00:17:35,754
so always throw them out
when they're spoiled.

409
00:17:35,821 --> 00:17:38,057
-He's like a school nurse.
-He's right.

410
00:17:38,624 --> 00:17:39,858
He told us to throw it out.

411
00:17:39,925 --> 00:17:41,427
-Please do that. I'm sorry.
-I'll throw it out.

412
00:17:41,493 --> 00:17:43,429
-Please do that.
-I'll throw the spoiled veggies out.

413
00:17:43,495 --> 00:17:45,197
I think I smell something weird.

414
00:17:45,264 --> 00:17:48,434
Let's check out the fridge first.
The bottom portion.

415
00:17:48,500 --> 00:17:50,602
-I see some cheese.
-Cheese.

416
00:17:50,669 --> 00:17:52,571
The hosts won't go any closer.

417
00:17:54,706 --> 00:17:58,577
I figured it out
as soon as I saw the arugula.

418
00:17:58,644 --> 00:18:00,145
I can't go closer.

419
00:18:00,212 --> 00:18:01,914
-We should be careful.
-I'm sorry.

420
00:18:01,980 --> 00:18:05,117
First of all,
let's find out what's in this container.

421
00:18:06,018 --> 00:18:08,220
-Why are you so scared?
-What's in here?

422
00:18:08,287 --> 00:18:10,289
-Be careful. It might burst.
-Is it kimchi?

423
00:18:10,355 --> 00:18:12,024
What is this?

424
00:18:12,091 --> 00:18:14,226
-Kimchi.
-It's kimchi.

425
00:18:14,293 --> 00:18:15,828
Kimchi should be fine.

426
00:18:15,894 --> 00:18:17,396
-Kimchi is…
-What if it isn't?

427
00:18:17,463 --> 00:18:18,897
It smells sour.

428
00:18:18,964 --> 00:18:20,466
-Is that kimchi?
-It is.

429
00:18:20,532 --> 00:18:22,101
Do you serve it in a separate dish?

430
00:18:22,167 --> 00:18:25,070
-I don't.
-You don't?

431
00:18:25,137 --> 00:18:27,406
It'll taste great as jjigae.

432
00:18:27,473 --> 00:18:30,509
-Is it okay?
-It's not okay.

433
00:18:30,576 --> 00:18:33,545
-It's not?
-Why not? It'd be great as jjigae.

434
00:18:33,612 --> 00:18:35,514
-No, it's fine.
-It's fine, right?

435
00:18:35,581 --> 00:18:37,916
That side says no,
but this side says okay.

436
00:18:38,584 --> 00:18:40,986
Goodness. It's fine.

437
00:18:41,053 --> 00:18:42,921
-It's fine.
-This is fine.

438
00:18:42,988 --> 00:18:46,758
They're the new gen,
and these are the fermented gen.

439
00:18:46,825 --> 00:18:49,828
-I see some doenjang jjigae paste.
-Yes.

440
00:18:49,895 --> 00:18:51,763
-It expired.
-We're past this date.

441
00:18:51,830 --> 00:18:54,967
-Again?
-It expired on November 30th, 2024.

442
00:18:55,033 --> 00:18:58,504
-Doenjang should be fine.
-Isn't doenjang all right?

443
00:18:58,570 --> 00:18:59,705
-She used some.
-She used a lot.

444
00:18:59,771 --> 00:19:02,307
She did, but I also saw a lot of soup.

445
00:19:03,609 --> 00:19:05,611
-But doenjang can't go that bad.
-It's fine.

446
00:19:05,677 --> 00:19:08,347
-Is it? Is doenjang okay?
-It's fine.

447
00:19:08,413 --> 00:19:09,648
You said there was soup.

448
00:19:09,715 --> 00:19:11,783
Will you just do it there
instead of bringing it over?

449
00:19:12,417 --> 00:19:14,019
There's soup in this container.

450
00:19:14,086 --> 00:19:16,188
-Why do you keep bringing it?
-Just throw it out.

451
00:19:16,255 --> 00:19:17,723
-Right?
-Throw it out.

452
00:19:17,789 --> 00:19:19,591
THE DOENJANG JJIGAE PASTE
WITH SOUP, OUT

453
00:19:20,459 --> 00:19:22,628
Will Eun-ji be okay?

454
00:19:22,694 --> 00:19:23,862
I guess she cooks at times.

455
00:19:23,929 --> 00:19:26,365
-There are lots of ingredients.
-Yes. Minced garlic.

456
00:19:26,431 --> 00:19:29,468
The minced garlic is quite frozen.

457
00:19:29,535 --> 00:19:31,236
-They're about to get powdered.
-Has it been too long?

458
00:19:31,303 --> 00:19:32,471
It's too dry.

459
00:19:32,538 --> 00:19:35,340
-It's brown. The colors changed.
-Right? She can't use this.

460
00:19:35,407 --> 00:19:37,409
-It's better not to use that.
-Throw it out.

461
00:19:37,476 --> 00:19:39,478
MINCED GARLIC, OUT

462
00:19:39,545 --> 00:19:41,780
Gosh, this one.

463
00:19:41,847 --> 00:19:43,182
I have to throw that out.

464
00:19:43,248 --> 00:19:45,984
She should've had this
until December 6th, 2024.

465
00:19:46,885 --> 00:19:49,655
PLEASE THROW THAT OUT

466
00:19:50,155 --> 00:19:51,857
Throw it out.

467
00:19:51,924 --> 00:19:53,425
This isn't <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>,

468
00:19:53,492 --> 00:19:55,861
but more like <i>Clean Up My Fridge</i>.

469
00:19:55,928 --> 00:19:59,498
We should clean it out, though.
These could make you sick.

470
00:19:59,565 --> 00:20:00,699
HMM…

471
00:20:00,766 --> 00:20:01,833
SNIFFLE…

472
00:20:01,900 --> 00:20:03,902
-Are you crying?
-No.

473
00:20:03,969 --> 00:20:05,938
WHAT'S IN HER FRIDGE
MAKES HIM WANT TO CRY

474
00:20:06,004 --> 00:20:07,072
All right.

475
00:20:07,139 --> 00:20:09,441
I see. There are vegetables.

476
00:20:09,508 --> 00:20:13,979
That's a pack of garnishes for steak.

477
00:20:14,046 --> 00:20:16,415
-At times, I'd grill steak at home.
-Right.

478
00:20:16,481 --> 00:20:18,784
-And you serve it with these garnishes.
-Yes.

479
00:20:18,850 --> 00:20:21,420
I guess there are fruit flies now
after we opened my fridge.

480
00:20:21,486 --> 00:20:23,055
Chef Yeon-bok keeps catching them.

481
00:20:23,121 --> 00:20:25,224
THE CHEF CATCHES FRUIT FLIES

482
00:20:25,290 --> 00:20:26,692
These look okay.

483
00:20:26,758 --> 00:20:29,828
We don't have anything we can use
among the food you showed us.

484
00:20:29,895 --> 00:20:32,965
-It smells good. I think it'll be fine.
-It looks fine.

485
00:20:33,031 --> 00:20:34,700
-It's okay.
-It is, right?

486
00:20:34,766 --> 00:20:36,001
But I won't use these.

487
00:20:36,068 --> 00:20:38,537
-You said these were fine. How many?
-Why not?

488
00:20:38,604 --> 00:20:40,973
-Whoa.
-No one wants them.

489
00:20:41,039 --> 00:20:43,575
MIMICKING KANG-ROK

490
00:20:43,642 --> 00:20:45,577
-I'll use these.
-You will?

491
00:20:45,644 --> 00:20:48,447
-These look fine.
-These look fine. They aren't gone.

492
00:20:48,513 --> 00:20:50,983
-She said it was fine.
-It was better than we expected.

493
00:20:51,049 --> 00:20:52,551
These pickles look fine.

494
00:20:52,618 --> 00:20:54,853
-The pickles made it.
-They made it?

495
00:20:54,920 --> 00:20:56,755
-They made it.
-They're fresh.

496
00:20:56,822 --> 00:20:59,191
-She didn't even open it.
-I'm glad.

497
00:20:59,258 --> 00:21:01,393
-I'm worried about the lower shelf.
-Yes.

498
00:21:01,460 --> 00:21:02,861
That plastic bag made me worried.

499
00:21:05,030 --> 00:21:07,766
-It's fine. You can touch that.
-Cilantro.

500
00:21:07,833 --> 00:21:10,502
-Cilantro. She likes cilantro.
-I love cilantro.

501
00:21:10,569 --> 00:21:12,671
-The cilantro looks fine.
-Cilantro.

502
00:21:12,738 --> 00:21:15,507
-This must be jokbal, braised pigs' feet.
-This is…

503
00:21:15,574 --> 00:21:18,310
I had that about two days ago.

504
00:21:18,377 --> 00:21:21,346
-Is that okay?
-Yes, you can just eat it now. It's fine.

505
00:21:22,114 --> 00:21:23,248
-It's fine.
-It is.

506
00:21:23,315 --> 00:21:25,751
-It's totally fine.
-It is.

507
00:21:25,817 --> 00:21:27,786
I love to eat jokbal with cilantro.

508
00:21:27,853 --> 00:21:29,588
-That sounds good.
-Jokbal with cilantro?

509
00:21:29,655 --> 00:21:31,890
-Whoa.
-Jokbal with cilantro.

510
00:21:31,957 --> 00:21:33,759
Let's move on to the freezer.

511
00:21:33,825 --> 00:21:35,727
Let me pull these out first.

512
00:21:35,794 --> 00:21:37,562
ALREADY EMBARRASSED

513
00:21:37,629 --> 00:21:39,498
She has lots of stuff.

514
00:21:39,564 --> 00:21:41,867
-What's that?
-What is that?

515
00:21:41,933 --> 00:21:45,270
It's full of frost. What is this?

516
00:21:45,337 --> 00:21:47,706
Wait, did you leave food waste in here?

517
00:21:47,773 --> 00:21:49,708
-Is this okay, Eun-ji?
-Is this food waste?

518
00:21:49,775 --> 00:21:50,776
What's this?

519
00:21:50,842 --> 00:21:53,045
What's this? This is trash.

520
00:21:54,279 --> 00:21:56,782
This is food waste.

521
00:21:56,848 --> 00:21:59,017
-There's something I want to mention.
-Yes?

522
00:21:59,084 --> 00:22:00,952
The expiration date
and use by date are different.

523
00:22:01,019 --> 00:22:04,189
You can eat your food
a bit longer than the expiration date

524
00:22:04,256 --> 00:22:08,393
-only if it's stored properly.
-It's not. It's just thrown in here.

525
00:22:08,460 --> 00:22:12,130
But Eun-ji stashed those in
without sealing them up.

526
00:22:12,197 --> 00:22:14,499
Am I on <i>Dr. Oh's Golden Clinic</i>?

527
00:22:15,801 --> 00:22:19,471
What's wrong with my choice
to use my fridge like that?

528
00:22:19,538 --> 00:22:22,341
-You should stay healthy, so throw it out.
-Thanks. All right.

529
00:22:22,407 --> 00:22:25,310
-You have some meat.
-Meat, yes. I had some?

530
00:22:25,377 --> 00:22:26,945
-You had meat.
-"I had some?"

531
00:22:27,012 --> 00:22:30,148
-You do have some meat.
-Yes, you have what you need.

532
00:22:30,215 --> 00:22:31,550
-Is this kimchi?
-Tteokbokki.

533
00:22:31,616 --> 00:22:33,251
-No, tteokbokki.
-Tteokbokki.

534
00:22:34,386 --> 00:22:35,887
I divided it into small portions.

535
00:22:35,954 --> 00:22:38,924
-It's not that old.
-It's frozen.

536
00:22:38,990 --> 00:22:41,660
-But you portioned these to save them all.
-This is the same.

537
00:22:41,727 --> 00:22:45,731
I like refreshingly spicy dishes.

538
00:22:45,797 --> 00:22:48,667
Hey, I found this.

539
00:22:48,734 --> 00:22:51,370
-What's that?
-Choi Hyun-suk's meal kit.

540
00:22:51,436 --> 00:22:52,437
It's really good.

541
00:22:52,504 --> 00:22:56,441
I eat Chef Hyun-suk's food
about three times a week.

542
00:22:56,508 --> 00:22:57,876
Thank you, my customer.

543
00:22:59,611 --> 00:23:02,114
It's really good,
so you can use it as you like.

544
00:23:02,180 --> 00:23:05,050
-Chef Hyun-suk already did it.
-Send me some.

545
00:23:05,117 --> 00:23:07,486
What are these? French fries?

546
00:23:07,552 --> 00:23:09,087
-French fries.
-French fries.

547
00:23:09,154 --> 00:23:10,389
The French fries are frozen?

548
00:23:10,989 --> 00:23:12,657
-French fries.
-Is it okay to do that?

549
00:23:12,724 --> 00:23:15,193
-How are you going to eat that?
-How do you eat it again?

550
00:23:15,260 --> 00:23:17,429
I open the bag, throw olive oil in…

551
00:23:17,496 --> 00:23:19,731
-And mix.
-…shake it around, pour it in,

552
00:23:19,798 --> 00:23:21,800
push the button,
open a can of beer, and go…

553
00:23:21,867 --> 00:23:24,102
Everything else is fine,

554
00:23:24,169 --> 00:23:25,437
but it's really bad for your health

555
00:23:25,504 --> 00:23:27,172
to reheat French fries

556
00:23:27,239 --> 00:23:29,374
because they create carcinogens.

557
00:23:29,441 --> 00:23:32,711
-Okay, Mom.
-But it's more delicious to do that.

558
00:23:32,778 --> 00:23:34,279
"Okay, Mom."

559
00:23:34,346 --> 00:23:35,747
So? Throw them out? Leave them?

560
00:23:35,814 --> 00:23:37,549
-Leave them. I'll eat those.
-"Leave them."

561
00:23:37,616 --> 00:23:40,085
I'll eat like that just for a day.

562
00:23:40,919 --> 00:23:42,454
THE PROBLEMATIC
FRIDGE OWNER PROTESTS

563
00:23:42,521 --> 00:23:44,823
The fridge owner is
fighting with the chef.

564
00:23:44,890 --> 00:23:47,426
It's not like
I eat like that every single day.

565
00:23:48,126 --> 00:23:53,098
It feels like seeing a problematic kid
talking to Dr. Oh Hyun-suk.

566
00:23:53,165 --> 00:23:55,734
"Dr. Oh Hyun-suk"?

567
00:23:55,801 --> 00:23:57,235
She has lots of food. It's great.

568
00:23:57,302 --> 00:23:59,037
Chefs, did you all take a good look?

569
00:23:59,104 --> 00:24:00,806
That was the problematic fridge.

570
00:24:00,872 --> 00:24:03,875
-Let the 15-minute cook-off begin!
-Begin!

571
00:24:05,944 --> 00:24:06,945
Let us begin the round

572
00:24:07,012 --> 00:24:10,949
for the order
"hello, it's me. Any bar snacks there?"

573
00:24:11,016 --> 00:24:15,253
The fastest chef in <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>,
Chef Yeon-bok.

574
00:24:15,320 --> 00:24:20,559
He's up against Chef Kang-rok,
the slowest chef on the show.

575
00:24:20,625 --> 00:24:22,427
I'm just sharing my observations.

576
00:24:22,494 --> 00:24:23,829
Oh, no.

577
00:24:23,895 --> 00:24:25,597
Now that they're against each other,

578
00:24:25,664 --> 00:24:27,399
-I realized their names sound similar.
-Do they?

579
00:24:27,466 --> 00:24:29,201
Rok and Bok, Bok and Rok.

580
00:24:29,267 --> 00:24:30,469
They're Roki and Boki.

581
00:24:30,535 --> 00:24:32,938
-They're Roki and Boki.
-Yes.

582
00:24:33,004 --> 00:24:34,005
Yes, you're right.

583
00:24:34,072 --> 00:24:36,141
-They're a good match.
-Who'll be lucky?

584
00:24:36,208 --> 00:24:37,709
So far, Chef Kang-rok

585
00:24:37,776 --> 00:24:40,645
has lost twice against Chef Ho-young.

586
00:24:40,712 --> 00:24:42,547
2 ROUNDS, 2 CONSECUTIVE LOSSES
AGAINST JUNG HO-YOUNG

587
00:24:42,614 --> 00:24:44,149
He's desperate for his first win,

588
00:24:44,216 --> 00:24:46,785
but he's up against
the strongest contender, Chef Yeon-bok.

589
00:24:47,786 --> 00:24:50,522
How do you feel, Chef Kang-rok?

590
00:24:50,589 --> 00:24:52,657
First of all, it feels devastating.

591
00:24:53,525 --> 00:24:54,626
He feels devastated.

592
00:24:54,693 --> 00:24:56,194
-We haven't even begun.
-Oh, no.

593
00:24:56,261 --> 00:24:59,197
-So?
-I'd like to tell Chef Sung-jun

594
00:24:59,264 --> 00:25:01,600
that I'll record three losses first.

595
00:25:02,534 --> 00:25:04,336
-Is this our fight?
-He already feels like he lost.

596
00:25:04,402 --> 00:25:07,072
-You can't give up before you begin.
-You haven't started.

597
00:25:07,138 --> 00:25:09,674
You're the captain,
so you must lead the team to victory.

598
00:25:09,741 --> 00:25:11,042
Yes, he's the captain.

599
00:25:11,109 --> 00:25:12,110
GLANCES

600
00:25:12,878 --> 00:25:15,213
Would you feel like that
if you were in my shoes?

601
00:25:16,548 --> 00:25:18,250
-Oh, no.
-My gosh.

602
00:25:18,316 --> 00:25:20,585
-You never know.
-It'll be huge if you win.

603
00:25:20,652 --> 00:25:22,954
-Do your best.
-You haven't tried yet.

604
00:25:23,021 --> 00:25:25,891
You even washed your cap
before you came here.

605
00:25:25,957 --> 00:25:27,225
SPARKLING CLEAN

606
00:25:27,292 --> 00:25:29,427
-He's here to turn over a new leaf.
-Yes.

607
00:25:29,494 --> 00:25:31,963
Now, you have to make something
to eat with a drink.

608
00:25:32,030 --> 00:25:34,733
Chef Kang-rok,
do you drink alone from time to time?

609
00:25:34,799 --> 00:25:36,268
After coming here

610
00:25:36,334 --> 00:25:40,372
and doing these 15-minute cook-offs,

611
00:25:40,438 --> 00:25:41,606
I began to drink a bit more.

612
00:25:43,208 --> 00:25:45,176
-Oh, no.
-He's drinking more.

613
00:25:45,243 --> 00:25:46,645
And I talk to myself.

614
00:25:46,711 --> 00:25:49,114
-And he talks to himself?
-He talks to himself.

615
00:25:49,180 --> 00:25:51,516
-I'd go, "Why did you do that?"
-He talks to himself.

616
00:25:51,583 --> 00:25:56,087
Then you'd know the perfect dishes
for people who drink alone at home.

617
00:25:57,122 --> 00:25:59,291
The best chaser is loneliness.

618
00:25:59,357 --> 00:26:01,126
Loneliness.

619
00:26:01,192 --> 00:26:02,761
That was a golden quote.

620
00:26:02,827 --> 00:26:04,963
I had a brief talk with her,

621
00:26:06,431 --> 00:26:07,599
and she seemed lonely.

622
00:26:07,666 --> 00:26:11,202
-I see. Me?
-You seemed lonesome.

623
00:26:11,269 --> 00:26:13,605
But I don't feel so lonely now.

624
00:26:13,672 --> 00:26:15,340
SHE'S WITH CHEF DOUBLE STARS

625
00:26:15,407 --> 00:26:17,609
You can still use your perk.

626
00:26:17,676 --> 00:26:21,546
You can either begin a minute earlier
or stop him for a minute.

627
00:26:21,613 --> 00:26:23,548
Now, will you use the perk?

628
00:26:23,615 --> 00:26:25,684
-No, I won't.
-What?

629
00:26:25,750 --> 00:26:27,152
-Why not?
-You won't?

630
00:26:27,218 --> 00:26:30,488
No, when I used it
against Chef Ho-young,

631
00:26:30,555 --> 00:26:33,058
-his salsa dance was too shocking.
-The salsa dance.

632
00:26:33,124 --> 00:26:34,693
He's not supposed to cross over.

633
00:26:34,759 --> 00:26:36,061
GETTING DIZZY

634
00:26:36,127 --> 00:26:37,529
You won't have to worry about that.

635
00:26:37,596 --> 00:26:40,865
-Why would I do the salsa dance there?
-He usually stays still.

636
00:26:40,932 --> 00:26:43,168
But as I mentioned last time,

637
00:26:43,234 --> 00:26:44,869
I dread drawing attention.

638
00:26:44,936 --> 00:26:46,538
He hated that even more.

639
00:26:46,605 --> 00:26:47,973
-For a minute.
-He's right.

640
00:26:48,807 --> 00:26:50,642
CHEF CHOI KANG-ROK'S INGREDIENTS:
SCALLOP PASTA MEAL KIT, ASPARAGUS,

641
00:26:50,709 --> 00:26:52,544
SOUS VIDE CHICKEN BREAST, PEPERONCINO,
SEASONED VICTORY ONION, AND MORE

642
00:26:52,611 --> 00:26:56,147
CHEF YEON-BOK'S INGREDIENTS:

643
00:26:56,214 --> 00:26:59,751
OLIVE OIL, STRIP LOIN,
OYSTER SAUCE, CONDIMENT, CILANTRO

644
00:26:59,818 --> 00:27:01,252
First, Chef Yeon-bok.

645
00:27:01,319 --> 00:27:03,088
The dish I'll make is called

646
00:27:03,154 --> 00:27:06,224
One Slice, One Shot.

647
00:27:06,291 --> 00:27:08,126
NICE RHYME

648
00:27:08,193 --> 00:27:10,395
"One Slice, One Shot."

649
00:27:10,462 --> 00:27:14,332
I'll cover slices of meat
with seasoned rice powder and steam them.

650
00:27:14,399 --> 00:27:18,603
It'll taste delicious if you eat that
with some sauce and cilantro.

651
00:27:18,670 --> 00:27:19,671
He's using cilantro.

652
00:27:19,738 --> 00:27:21,840
My favorite bar snack is beef jeon.

653
00:27:21,906 --> 00:27:24,676
-I see.
-I think it'll be something like that.

654
00:27:24,743 --> 00:27:27,946
Chef Kang-rok, what's the dish you'll make
to fight against him?

655
00:27:28,747 --> 00:27:32,217
I'm going to braise something.

656
00:27:32,283 --> 00:27:33,618
I thought I should.

657
00:27:33,685 --> 00:27:35,553
-You'll braise?
-You will?

658
00:27:35,620 --> 00:27:36,788
He's finally doing it.

659
00:27:36,855 --> 00:27:38,256
-It's such an honor.
-His braise.

660
00:27:38,323 --> 00:27:39,991
BRAISED DISHES MADE HIM
THE WINNER OF A COOKING SHOW

661
00:27:40,058 --> 00:27:42,360
<i>He's braising oysters in perilla oil.</i>

662
00:27:42,427 --> 00:27:43,862
MR. BRAISE FINALLY DROPS
HIS BEST MOVE

663
00:27:43,928 --> 00:27:45,797
-You'll braise?
-You will?

664
00:27:45,864 --> 00:27:47,599
-He's finally doing it.
-It's such an honor.

665
00:27:47,666 --> 00:27:49,601
It's nothing special.

666
00:27:49,668 --> 00:27:51,202
I'm scared.

667
00:27:51,269 --> 00:27:53,972
-He'll finally braise something.
-He put everything into this.

668
00:27:54,039 --> 00:27:55,140
What's it called?

669
00:27:55,206 --> 00:27:56,775
WHAT'S THE DISH CALLED?

670
00:27:56,841 --> 00:27:59,177
I Am a Braised Human.

671
00:27:59,244 --> 00:28:01,446
-I Am a Braised Human.
-I Am a Braised Human.

672
00:28:01,513 --> 00:28:04,049
The dish is called I Am a Braised Human.

673
00:28:04,115 --> 00:28:06,051
Did you find anything worth braising?

674
00:28:06,117 --> 00:28:08,486
-She didn't have a particular ingredient.
-Right.

675
00:28:08,553 --> 00:28:11,756
So I want to braise ingredients in oil.

676
00:28:11,823 --> 00:28:13,191
-In oil?
-Braising in oil?

677
00:28:13,258 --> 00:28:14,526
-Wait, how?
-Can you elaborate?

678
00:28:14,592 --> 00:28:17,395
It's like gambas…

679
00:28:17,462 --> 00:28:19,397
gambas al ajillo.

680
00:28:19,464 --> 00:28:23,068
Ajillo is a dish you eat
by braising many ingredients in oil.

681
00:28:23,134 --> 00:28:24,703
Like aglio e olio.

682
00:28:24,769 --> 00:28:27,639
I thought you had to use soy sauce,
but that mustn't be it.

683
00:28:27,706 --> 00:28:31,543
There are many different types
of braised dishes.

684
00:28:32,043 --> 00:28:33,111
Think outside the box.

685
00:28:33,845 --> 00:28:35,180
ME?

686
00:28:35,246 --> 00:28:36,715
-Think outside the box.
-He found his confidence.

687
00:28:36,781 --> 00:28:38,349
The world of braising is different?

688
00:28:38,416 --> 00:28:40,118
Yes, it's more widely used in real life.

689
00:28:40,185 --> 00:28:42,253
-He's right.
-Real-life braising.

690
00:28:42,320 --> 00:28:43,722
The world of braising is broad.

691
00:28:43,788 --> 00:28:45,156
I saw that

692
00:28:45,223 --> 00:28:47,859
-you had your favorite meal kit.
-Yes.

693
00:28:47,926 --> 00:28:50,161
I saw that scallops were included.

694
00:28:50,228 --> 00:28:53,498
Yes, scallops of excellent quality are
included in that.

695
00:28:53,565 --> 00:28:54,566
NODDING

696
00:28:54,632 --> 00:28:55,633
Is that so?

697
00:28:55,700 --> 00:28:58,603
I want to braise
this and that in her fridge

698
00:28:58,670 --> 00:29:02,507
and make her crave some soju

699
00:29:02,574 --> 00:29:04,943
with a side of loneliness.

700
00:29:05,009 --> 00:29:06,611
I see.

701
00:29:06,678 --> 00:29:09,314
And now, let us begin the round

702
00:29:09,380 --> 00:29:14,385
with Eun-ji's order,
"Hello, it's me. Any bar snacks there?"

703
00:29:15,286 --> 00:29:17,589
The fastest chef on <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>,

704
00:29:17,655 --> 00:29:21,593
Chef Lee Yeon-bok,
also known as Usain Bok-t.

705
00:29:21,659 --> 00:29:24,295
He's up against
the slowest chef on <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>,

706
00:29:24,362 --> 00:29:29,400
slower than a tortoise, Mr. Slow,
Chef Choi Kang-rok.

707
00:29:29,467 --> 00:29:33,505
Who'll be the winner
among the two polar opposites?

708
00:29:34,973 --> 00:29:36,474
-Can you hold it here?
-Who'll be

709
00:29:36,541 --> 00:29:37,675
-the winner?
-Like this?

710
00:29:37,742 --> 00:29:41,412
Let the 15-minute cook-off begin!

711
00:29:42,213 --> 00:29:44,516
<i>Hello, it's me</i>

712
00:29:44,582 --> 00:29:48,720
<i>Hello, it's me</i>

713
00:29:48,787 --> 00:29:53,091
<i>Any bar snacks there?</i>

714
00:29:53,158 --> 00:29:55,293
-She's a good singer.
-Good luck!

715
00:29:55,794 --> 00:29:57,929
Eun-ji and Chef Jong-won are a good match.

716
00:29:57,996 --> 00:29:59,097
-Yes.
-Totally.

717
00:29:59,164 --> 00:30:02,333
THE COOK-OFF BEGINS
WITH HER SWEET(?) SUPPORT

