-What?

959
00:39:55,559 --> 00:39:56,894
-Gosh!
-The bell.

960
00:39:56,961 --> 00:39:58,362
-You have to hit the bell.
-Gosh!

961
00:39:58,429 --> 00:40:00,698
-What's wrong? What's missing?
-What's wrong?

962
00:40:00,765 --> 00:40:02,600
I forgot to use the victory onion.

963
00:40:02,666 --> 00:40:04,735
-What's going on?
-What's missing?

964
00:40:04,802 --> 00:40:06,971
-The victory onion.
-My gosh.

965
00:40:07,037 --> 00:40:08,906
Announcer Jang!

966
00:40:08,973 --> 00:40:12,543
Go over to the scene.
Go over to Chef Kang-rok.

967
00:40:12,610 --> 00:40:15,713
-I'm here. What are you doing?
-You have 26 seconds.

968
00:40:15,780 --> 00:40:17,548
-I'm here.
-You have 26 seconds.

969
00:40:17,615 --> 00:40:19,550
-What are you doing?
-What did he miss?

970
00:40:19,617 --> 00:40:21,919
I left out victory onion.

971
00:40:21,986 --> 00:40:23,621
-Twenty seconds.
-Twenty seconds left.

972
00:40:23,687 --> 00:40:25,156
Twenty seconds.

973
00:40:25,222 --> 00:40:28,526
You have to wrap this up now.

974
00:40:28,592 --> 00:40:31,629
-She's right! You have 14 seconds!
-You have to hurry!

975
00:40:31,695 --> 00:40:33,731
Hurry up, 14 seconds.

976
00:40:33,798 --> 00:40:35,332
-Twelve. Eleven.
-Hit the bell!

977
00:40:35,399 --> 00:40:37,134
Chef Kang-rok finishes first!

978
00:40:37,201 --> 00:40:39,670
HE FINISHES BEFORE CHEF YEON-BOK

979
00:40:40,237 --> 00:40:42,540
Mr. Slow did it for the first time!

980
00:40:43,274 --> 00:40:45,509
-Seven. Six.
-Mr. Slow did it for the first time!

981
00:40:45,576 --> 00:40:47,378
-Five. Four.
-Five. Four.

982
00:40:47,445 --> 00:40:49,213
-Three. Two.
-Three. Two.

983
00:40:49,280 --> 00:40:51,348
-Three. Two.
-Three. Two.

984
00:40:51,415 --> 00:40:52,716
-One.
-One. The end!

985
00:40:52,783 --> 00:40:54,418
LEE YEON-BOK FINISHES
ONE SLICE, ONE SHOT

986
00:40:54,485 --> 00:40:55,920
It's over!

987
00:40:55,986 --> 00:40:57,488
-Gosh.
-It's all done.

988
00:40:57,555 --> 00:40:58,823
Great job, Announcer Jang.

989
00:40:58,889 --> 00:41:00,891
-Thank you.
-Great job!

990
00:41:00,958 --> 00:41:02,760
She's good at this.

991
00:41:03,861 --> 00:41:06,430
Gosh, everyone was amazing.

992
00:41:06,497 --> 00:41:08,132
You can do this! Whoa!

993
00:41:08,199 --> 00:41:09,433
You can do this! Whoa!

994
00:41:09,500 --> 00:41:10,734
STUMBLE

995
00:41:10,801 --> 00:41:13,504
You almost fell
because you had your eyes on the camera!

996
00:41:14,305 --> 00:41:15,573
Please have a seat.

997
00:41:15,639 --> 00:41:17,475
-Great job.
-Be careful.

998
00:41:17,975 --> 00:41:21,545
They both finished making
these dishes for Eun-ji.

999
00:41:21,612 --> 00:41:24,181
I'm so grateful,
yet I feel sorry for the chefs

1000
00:41:24,248 --> 00:41:26,917
because I didn't have enough ingredients.

1001
00:41:26,984 --> 00:41:30,054
I'm sorry for giving you such a huge task,
and thank you.

1002
00:41:30,120 --> 00:41:32,389
DON'T MENTION IT

1003
00:41:32,456 --> 00:41:35,092
Chef Kang-rok,
was it that hard to find ingredients?

1004
00:41:36,994 --> 00:41:38,863
I love you, meal kit.

1005
00:41:40,397 --> 00:41:41,966
WHAT WOULD HE HAVE DONE
WITHOUT IT?

1006
00:41:42,032 --> 00:41:44,034
-That was a great quote.
-It would've been trouble without it.

1007
00:41:44,101 --> 00:41:46,003
-I love you, meal kit.
-It would've been trouble.

1008
00:41:46,070 --> 00:41:49,039
Please have a taste
of Chef Kang-rok's dish first.

1009
00:41:49,106 --> 00:41:50,774
A CULINARY TRIP TO SPAIN!

1010
00:41:51,542 --> 00:41:54,678
ENJOY DIFFERENT INGREDIENTS
BRAISED IN OLIVE OIL

1011
00:41:55,246 --> 00:41:58,382
WITH FRIED RAMYEON(?), NOT BREAD!

1012
00:41:59,049 --> 00:42:02,119
CHEF CHOI KANG-ROK'S I AM A BRAISED HUMAN

1013
00:42:02,186 --> 00:42:04,722
-Oh, my gosh.
-Gosh.

1014
00:42:04,788 --> 00:42:06,657
One of my favorite bar snacks is

1015
00:42:06,724 --> 00:42:08,993
something hot and hearty

1016
00:42:09,059 --> 00:42:11,028
like seafood soup with scorched rice.

1017
00:42:11,095 --> 00:42:12,897
-It looks so good.
-I think it's like that.

1018
00:42:12,963 --> 00:42:17,501
-There's a good amount of oil underneath.
-There is.

1019
00:42:17,568 --> 00:42:21,071
First, I'll top it
with a piece of chicken breast.

1020
00:42:21,138 --> 00:42:22,940
I'll add a piece of asparagus too.

1021
00:42:23,007 --> 00:42:24,708
I'll try it like this, Chef Kang-rok.

1022
00:42:24,775 --> 00:42:26,176
It looks good.

1023
00:42:26,243 --> 00:42:28,078
It's dripping with oil.

1024
00:42:28,145 --> 00:42:30,180
-It must be hot.
-Yes.

1025
00:42:30,681 --> 00:42:33,350
-Okay, Eun-ji.
-I heard a crunchy sound.

1026
00:42:34,318 --> 00:42:35,619
-A crunchy sound?
-Yes.

1027
00:42:35,686 --> 00:42:37,021
CRUNCH

1028
00:42:37,087 --> 00:42:39,790
<i>Hello, it's me</i>

1029
00:42:39,857 --> 00:42:41,325
-It must be good.
-Hello?

1030
00:42:41,392 --> 00:42:43,561
Hello? How is it?

1031
00:42:44,395 --> 00:42:47,431
-Her lips look so greasy.
-Eun-ji, your chin.

1032
00:42:49,333 --> 00:42:50,968
My gosh!

1033
00:42:51,902 --> 00:42:53,470
SURPRISED GUY 1, 2

1034
00:42:53,537 --> 00:42:55,272
Where did you find that soju?

1035
00:42:55,339 --> 00:42:58,275
-She brought it here.
-My gosh.

1036
00:42:58,342 --> 00:42:59,977
May I have it like how I do it alone?

1037
00:43:00,044 --> 00:43:02,646
-Yes, as you like.
-Please do it as you do at home.

1038
00:43:02,713 --> 00:43:03,981
How I do it at home?

1039
00:43:05,149 --> 00:43:06,483
That was your order.

1040
00:43:06,550 --> 00:43:08,519
-I sit like this.
-I see.

1041
00:43:08,586 --> 00:43:11,722
She came home after a tough shoot.

1042
00:43:11,789 --> 00:43:12,990
She was quite stressed out.

1043
00:43:13,057 --> 00:43:14,558
Nothing is in her way now.

1044
00:43:14,625 --> 00:43:16,026
My gosh.

1045
00:43:16,093 --> 00:43:20,764
Everyone, this is her order,
so please do understand.

1046
00:43:20,831 --> 00:43:22,299
-Please understand.
-Eun-ji's serious.

1047
00:43:23,667 --> 00:43:25,769
-My gosh.
-Jeez.

1048
00:43:25,836 --> 00:43:27,404
-Goodness.
-Yes.

1049
00:43:28,138 --> 00:43:30,975
I wonder if it goes well with soju.

1050
00:43:31,041 --> 00:43:32,710
How is it with soju?

1051
00:43:32,776 --> 00:43:34,078
It's so good.

1052
00:43:35,079 --> 00:43:37,414
-Gosh, it's just so good.
-I see.

1053
00:43:37,481 --> 00:43:39,049
I wouldn't feel as guilty

1054
00:43:39,116 --> 00:43:40,618
if I had this with soju.

1055
00:43:40,684 --> 00:43:42,219
It almost feels healthy.

1056
00:43:42,286 --> 00:43:46,423
This mix of oil and vegetable
makes a wonderful dish.

1057
00:43:46,490 --> 00:43:48,726
-And garlic.
-Toward the end,

1058
00:43:48,792 --> 00:43:51,095
he quickly threw in
some victory onion, right?

1059
00:43:51,161 --> 00:43:53,197
-Just before he hit the bell.
-Yes.

1060
00:43:53,263 --> 00:43:55,265
-That adds such a kick.
-It does?

1061
00:43:55,332 --> 00:43:59,536
And the noodles. We were worried
what he'd do with those at first.

1062
00:43:59,603 --> 00:44:01,138
-The fresh noodles.
-Yes, the fresh noodles.

1063
00:44:01,205 --> 00:44:04,875
But it tastes chewy yet crunchy.

1064
00:44:04,942 --> 00:44:08,212
-He gave new life to pasta.
-Yes, something like that.

1065
00:44:08,278 --> 00:44:11,582
-She's having a scallop and victory onion.
-It looks so good.

1066
00:44:12,583 --> 00:44:14,952
Yes, after a long day…

1067
00:44:15,019 --> 00:44:16,787
Look at how she's frowning.

1068
00:44:16,854 --> 00:44:18,522
-It's that delicious.
-It makes her frown.

1069
00:44:18,589 --> 00:44:21,659
Look at how serious she looks.
How was that?

1070
00:44:21,725 --> 00:44:23,761
-Yet another shot.
-Oh, no.

1071
00:44:25,329 --> 00:44:27,531
Let's move on before she gets drunk.

1072
00:44:27,598 --> 00:44:28,899
He's opening it.

1073
00:44:28,966 --> 00:44:30,901
-My gosh.
-What was that?

1074
00:44:30,968 --> 00:44:32,469
He's opening it.

1075
00:44:32,536 --> 00:44:34,838
-My gosh.
-What was that?

1076
00:44:34,905 --> 00:44:36,240
The rice powder looks fresh.

1077
00:44:36,306 --> 00:44:38,108
You'd love that.

1078
00:44:38,175 --> 00:44:40,811
This time, she'll try

1079
00:44:40,878 --> 00:44:42,880
Chef Yeon-bok's One Slice, One Shot.

1080
00:44:44,081 --> 00:44:46,517
SERVED WITH SPICY AND SOUR
CHINESE-STYLE SAUCE

1081
00:44:47,751 --> 00:44:51,722
CHEF LEE YEON-BOK'S
ONE SLICE, ONE SHOT

1082
00:44:52,356 --> 00:44:56,226
It already smells like
it's full of all of my favorites.

1083
00:44:56,293 --> 00:44:59,196
-Cilantro. Green onion.
-And green onion.

1084
00:44:59,263 --> 00:45:04,401
He ground up soaked rice
and put it on the meat.

1085
00:45:04,468 --> 00:45:07,838
-Was it cooked well?
-Totally. Can you see this?

1086
00:45:07,905 --> 00:45:10,240
I can see it.

1087
00:45:10,307 --> 00:45:11,475
I'll put it like this

1088
00:45:11,542 --> 00:45:13,077
-and top it with green onion.
-Yes.

1089
00:45:13,143 --> 00:45:14,278
And the sauce.

1090
00:45:14,344 --> 00:45:16,814
-Pick up mostly the veggies.
-The veggies.

1091
00:45:16,880 --> 00:45:21,251
Even when I had the sauce,
I knew it'd go well with meat.

1092
00:45:21,318 --> 00:45:23,420
It feels like a dish I need to eat

1093
00:45:23,487 --> 00:45:26,290
when I drink alone at home
after breaking up with my boyfriend.

1094
00:45:30,627 --> 00:45:32,096
She'll have it together.

1095
00:45:32,162 --> 00:45:33,530
IT CALLS FOR SOJU RIGHT AWAY

1096
00:45:33,597 --> 00:45:35,165
I got this feeling.

1097
00:45:35,232 --> 00:45:37,634
-I have to drink first.
-I see.

1098
00:45:40,104 --> 00:45:41,105
But soju…

1099
00:45:41,171 --> 00:45:43,907
-She keeps it in her mouth.
-What's with you?

1100
00:45:44,675 --> 00:45:47,344
-Eun-ji, you'll ruin your teeth.
-She's gargling.

1101
00:45:48,512 --> 00:45:50,314
She does that when she's bored.

1102
00:45:53,350 --> 00:45:54,351
SMILING

1103
00:45:56,987 --> 00:45:59,389
You broke up right now.
You were heartbroken.

1104
00:45:59,456 --> 00:46:02,826
-Your eyes are wet.
-Why are you laughing after a breakup?

1105
00:46:02,893 --> 00:46:04,094
Why do you laugh after a breakup?

1106
00:46:04,161 --> 00:46:05,796
Her eyes are crying,
but her lips are smiling.

1107
00:46:05,863 --> 00:46:08,065
-The rice is fine.
-It is?

1108
00:46:08,132 --> 00:46:09,333
It's cooked.

1109
00:46:09,399 --> 00:46:13,003
-It was just how he wanted it.
-Al dente.

1110
00:46:13,070 --> 00:46:14,571
When we eat rice in a stone pot,

1111
00:46:14,638 --> 00:46:17,441
-the top is deliciously undercooked.
-Undercooked.

1112
00:46:17,508 --> 00:46:20,844
And the green onion really did it.

1113
00:46:20,911 --> 00:46:23,046
This sauce is really good.

1114
00:46:23,113 --> 00:46:24,815
You have to try this sauce.

1115
00:46:24,882 --> 00:46:27,050
I see. Chef Kang-rok drops his head.

1116
00:46:27,117 --> 00:46:28,619
He's sighing.

1117
00:46:28,685 --> 00:46:32,422
His mood is swinging
according to Eun-ji's reaction.

1118
00:46:32,489 --> 00:46:34,291
But this dish was really good too.

1119
00:46:34,358 --> 00:46:35,859
I see. What will you do?

1120
00:46:35,926 --> 00:46:37,895
It's so hard to choose.

1121
00:46:37,961 --> 00:46:39,396
This is so good.

1122
00:46:39,463 --> 00:46:40,864
All right.

1123
00:46:40,931 --> 00:46:42,599
-Should we try it altogether?
-Okay.

1124
00:46:43,167 --> 00:46:44,268
RUNNING OVER

1125
00:46:44,868 --> 00:46:46,236
Are we all ready?

1126
00:46:46,303 --> 00:46:48,338
-My gosh.
-What's wrong?

1127
00:46:48,405 --> 00:46:49,940
Chef Hyun-suk ran over

1128
00:46:50,007 --> 00:46:53,443
looking like he anticipated
the dishes to be delicious.

1129
00:46:53,510 --> 00:46:54,745
-That was cute.
-He meant that.

1130
00:46:54,812 --> 00:46:56,847
-Yes.
-It was cute.

1131
00:46:56,914 --> 00:47:01,118
Let's try Chef Kang-rok's dish.
I Am a Braised Human.

1132
00:47:01,185 --> 00:47:03,086
Can we have a drink with it too?

1133
00:47:07,090 --> 00:47:08,959
I see. It's luxurious.

1134
00:47:10,127 --> 00:47:11,995
JANG-CHELIN AGREES

1135
00:47:12,062 --> 00:47:15,866
I thought we could only make braises
in soy sauce or gochujang.

1136
00:47:15,933 --> 00:47:17,835
There was a different dish.

1137
00:47:17,901 --> 00:47:20,537
There was. It tastes so mild.

1138
00:47:20,604 --> 00:47:23,574
I think he even mastered
how to braise oil.

1139
00:47:23,640 --> 00:47:26,109
He must be a true braised human.

1140
00:47:27,144 --> 00:47:29,012
-A true braised human.
-Braised human.

1141
00:47:29,079 --> 00:47:33,483
Next, Chef Yeon-bok's dish,
One Slice, One Shot.

1142
00:47:33,550 --> 00:47:35,152
<i>One shot</i>

1143
00:47:37,187 --> 00:47:38,755
Gosh, man.

1144
00:47:39,656 --> 00:47:41,458
-Should I give you some?
-No.

1145
00:47:41,525 --> 00:47:42,960
HE SMELLS IT FIRST

1146
00:47:43,026 --> 00:47:44,728
One slice, one shot.

1147
00:47:45,929 --> 00:47:49,733
The rice was… And the timing.

1148
00:47:51,802 --> 00:47:53,370
You eat it like you're studying.

1149
00:47:53,937 --> 00:47:55,172
It's interesting.

1150
00:47:55,973 --> 00:47:57,808
You're eating like you're at a library.

1151
00:47:57,875 --> 00:47:59,610
FINDS HIM INTERESTING

1152
00:48:01,078 --> 00:48:03,680
-Right?
-Hey, you two aren't here alone.

1153
00:48:03,747 --> 00:48:04,748
I'm sorry.

1154
00:48:06,083 --> 00:48:07,484
-Isn't it good?
-It's like he's studying.

1155
00:48:07,551 --> 00:48:08,552
Mmm.

1156
00:48:09,186 --> 00:48:10,587
Won-young, is the sauce spicy?

1157
00:48:10,654 --> 00:48:12,189
The moment I eat it,

1158
00:48:12,256 --> 00:48:14,758
<i>I can taste the pepper oil's flavor</i>
<i>more than its spiciness.</i>

1159
00:48:14,825 --> 00:48:17,227
<i>-And the sourness.</i>
<i>-And just the sourness.</i>

1160
00:48:17,294 --> 00:48:21,098
<i>This Chinese-style sauce</i>
<i>goes so well with meat.</i>

1161
00:48:21,164 --> 00:48:22,165
<i>It's so good.</i>

1162
00:48:22,232 --> 00:48:24,067
After work, it feels like

1163
00:48:24,134 --> 00:48:26,169
Chef Kang-rok's dish will say,

1164
00:48:26,236 --> 00:48:28,672
"Hey, you did a great job again today.
It must've been tough."

1165
00:48:28,739 --> 00:48:30,507
It feels like it's consoling me.

1166
00:48:30,574 --> 00:48:32,976
But Chef Yeon-bok's dish was like,

1167
00:48:33,043 --> 00:48:36,313
"Hey, that's not a big deal.
You'll be fine."

1168
00:48:36,380 --> 00:48:38,215
-"Eat this and cheer up."
-"Eat this and cheer up."

1169
00:48:38,282 --> 00:48:41,418
It felt like it consoled me
in that cool girl kind of way.

1170
00:48:41,485 --> 00:48:42,786
Okay, then.

1171
00:48:42,853 --> 00:48:45,822
-This is a tough one.
-It's time to decide.

1172
00:48:45,889 --> 00:48:48,125
Last time, Chef Yeon-bok suffered

1173
00:48:48,191 --> 00:48:50,794
from a huge loss
against his junior Chinese chef.

1174
00:48:50,861 --> 00:48:52,896
If Chef Kang-rok loses today,

1175
00:48:52,963 --> 00:48:55,065
he'd be the first chef

1176
00:48:55,132 --> 00:48:57,768
to lose three times in a row
in this new season.

1177
00:48:57,834 --> 00:49:00,971
We already had a chef
who won three times in a row,

1178
00:49:01,038 --> 00:49:02,706
but no one who lost three times.

1179
00:49:02,773 --> 00:49:05,575
-I can relate.
-A lot of things are at stake here.

1180
00:49:05,642 --> 00:49:08,145
-Just evaluate this on the taste.
-Just be yourself.

1181
00:49:08,211 --> 00:49:10,747
Number one, Lee Yeon-bok.

1182
00:49:10,814 --> 00:49:12,416
Number two, Choi Kang-rok.

1183
00:49:12,482 --> 00:49:14,251
Please press the button.

1184
00:49:14,318 --> 00:49:16,053
WHO DID EUN-JI CHOOSE?

1185
00:49:16,119 --> 00:49:17,120
Please press it.

1186
00:49:18,455 --> 00:49:19,456
HER SCREAM SHOWS HER AGONY

1187
00:49:19,523 --> 00:49:20,891
Stop whining.

1188
00:49:20,958 --> 00:49:22,492
Gosh, someone save me.

1189
00:49:22,559 --> 00:49:24,795
What do I do? I really can't choose.

1190
00:49:24,861 --> 00:49:26,296
-It's so hard.
-No one will protest

1191
00:49:26,363 --> 00:49:28,765
-against the fridge owner.
-This is hard.

1192
00:49:28,832 --> 00:49:31,234
Please press the button.

1193
00:49:32,002 --> 00:49:33,837
-I did.
-You did?

1194
00:49:33,904 --> 00:49:34,905
Let's find out.

1195
00:49:34,972 --> 00:49:37,441
Let's find out which one Eun-ji chose.

1196
00:49:37,507 --> 00:49:39,910
<i>Hello, it's me</i>

1197
00:49:39,977 --> 00:49:44,348
<i>Any bar snacks there?</i>

1198
00:49:44,414 --> 00:49:47,918
Will Lee Yeon-bok save his name?

1199
00:49:47,985 --> 00:49:50,320
Will Choi Kang-rok win for the first time?

1200
00:49:50,387 --> 00:49:52,990
Who did Eun-ji choose?

1201
00:49:53,056 --> 00:49:54,658
Who is it? Which one did you like better?

1202
00:49:55,359 --> 00:49:57,861
Who is it? Which one did you like better?

1203
00:50:00,097 --> 00:50:02,833
Who is it? Which one did you like better?

1204
00:50:02,899 --> 00:50:04,835
LEE YEON-BOK WINS

1205
00:50:04,901 --> 00:50:07,471
CHEF LEE YEON-BOK'S
ONE SLICE, ONE SHOT WINS

1206
00:50:07,537 --> 00:50:09,606
It was Lee Yeon-bok.

1207
00:50:09,673 --> 00:50:11,908
Lee Yeon-bok wins this round.

1208
00:50:11,975 --> 00:50:14,878
-Oh, no.
-Choi Kang-rok still has no stars.

1209
00:50:14,945 --> 00:50:16,279
Gosh, this is just wrong.

1210
00:50:16,346 --> 00:50:18,849
Oh, no.

1211
00:50:18,915 --> 00:50:21,985
It looks like he'll need more time
until the day breaks.

1212
00:50:22,052 --> 00:50:24,421
-Yes.
-He'll end up drinking more.

1213
00:50:24,488 --> 00:50:29,326
If I had to pick
only one of these to eat after work,

1214
00:50:29,393 --> 00:50:32,195
I thought I'd choose

1215
00:50:32,262 --> 00:50:36,066
something a little spicier
in my tired everyday life.

1216
00:50:36,133 --> 00:50:38,702
I'm sorry, but I think I'm a bit drunk.

1217
00:50:39,336 --> 00:50:40,337
Oh, no.

1218
00:50:40,404 --> 00:50:42,272
Here's a star for Chef Yeon-bok.

1219
00:50:42,339 --> 00:50:44,074
-Thank you.
-He has two wins now.

1220
00:50:44,141 --> 00:50:46,877
-Congratulations!
-Chef Yeon-bok!

1221
00:50:48,178 --> 00:50:51,548
Chef Yeon-bok has two stars now.
Congratulations.

1222
00:50:51,615 --> 00:50:55,452
<i>Let's begin the second round</i>
<i>with Eun-ji's ingredients.</i>

1223
00:50:55,519 --> 00:51:00,057
Chef Yeon-bok's two pupils are
up against each other.

1224
00:51:00,123 --> 00:51:02,392
The real pupil, Chef Jung Ji-sun

1225
00:51:02,459 --> 00:51:06,263
versus the knockoff pupil,
Webtoon Artist Kim Poong.

1226
00:51:06,329 --> 00:51:08,065
HIGHLY INTERESTED

1227
00:51:08,131 --> 00:51:09,833
I looked up the record

1228
00:51:09,900 --> 00:51:12,803
and saw that you two have fought before.

1229
00:51:12,869 --> 00:51:13,904
They have?

1230
00:51:13,970 --> 00:51:16,006
They fought just once.

1231
00:51:16,073 --> 00:51:18,141
The warrior is not scared of heat.

1232
00:51:18,208 --> 00:51:20,010
I have to jump.

1233
00:51:20,077 --> 00:51:21,978
<i>Back then, Artist Poong had won.</i>

1234
00:51:22,045 --> 00:51:23,380
-Really?
-Whoa.

1235
00:51:23,447 --> 00:51:25,115
The data shows his victory.

1236
00:51:25,182 --> 00:51:27,050
So, Chef Ji-sun must
save her face this time.

1237
00:51:27,117 --> 00:51:30,053
-She's here for revenge.
-I see.

1238
00:51:30,120 --> 00:51:31,855
I'm not who I used to be.

1239
00:51:31,922 --> 00:51:33,490
She's not the old Jung Ji-sun.

1240
00:51:33,557 --> 00:51:37,027
That's why I brought this lucky…

1241
00:51:37,094 --> 00:51:38,695
-The frying pan!
-You'll use it right away?

1242
00:51:38,762 --> 00:51:40,197
-My frying pan.
-You'll use it right away?

1243
00:51:40,263 --> 00:51:43,300
If I lose today, this frying pan will
have to retire.

1244
00:51:43,366 --> 00:51:44,801
Then let me have it.

1245
00:51:44,868 --> 00:51:47,671
-I'll give it to Poong.
-Yes!

1246
00:51:47,737 --> 00:51:50,207
IN THE END, HE LOST MISERABLY…

1247
00:51:50,273 --> 00:51:52,609
AND THE FRYING PAN
ENDED UP IN POONG'S HANDS

1248
00:51:52,676 --> 00:51:54,277
-I'll use it right away.
-Chef Sung-jun's pan.

1249
00:51:54,344 --> 00:51:55,946
I brought it here anyway.

1250
00:51:56,012 --> 00:51:58,548
I'll find out if this pan is lucky

1251
00:51:58,615 --> 00:52:00,383
or if it's cursed.

1252
00:52:00,450 --> 00:52:03,854
I'll test it out today.

1253
00:52:03,920 --> 00:52:05,555
If you lose today,

1254
00:52:05,622 --> 00:52:07,190
will you throw it out again?

1255
00:52:07,257 --> 00:52:09,059
Does anybody want this?

1256
00:52:09,759 --> 00:52:12,062
I'll pass it onto you.

1257
00:52:12,129 --> 00:52:13,597
-Oh, no.
-The pan did nothing wrong.

1258
00:52:13,663 --> 00:52:17,000
It'll keep going around
like that chain letter from England.

1259
00:52:17,067 --> 00:52:18,168
THE LUCKY CHAIN PAN

1260
00:52:18,235 --> 00:52:20,504
-The lucky pan.
-The lucky pan.

1261
00:52:20,570 --> 00:52:23,573
-Just watch. It'll end up with everyone.
-Oh, no.

1262
00:52:23,640 --> 00:52:26,409
The new chefs are allowed to use a perk.

1263
00:52:27,110 --> 00:52:29,045
-I won't use it.
-Whoa.

1264
00:52:29,112 --> 00:52:30,347
Why won't anyone use it?

1265
00:52:31,047 --> 00:52:32,082
That's so cool.

1266
00:52:32,149 --> 00:52:34,317
I came to win against him fair and square,

1267
00:52:34,384 --> 00:52:36,686
so I don't think I need to use that.

1268
00:52:36,753 --> 00:52:38,121
Then may I use it?

1269
00:52:39,256 --> 00:52:41,057
May I use it if we have leftover perks?

1270
00:52:41,124 --> 00:52:43,059
Just use your frying pan.

1271
00:52:43,126 --> 00:52:44,127
You can't do that.

1272
00:52:44,194 --> 00:52:46,363
He wants to use leftover perks?

1273
00:52:46,429 --> 00:52:50,567
A few chefs didn't benefit
from turning down the perk.

1274
00:52:50,634 --> 00:52:52,469
Chef Sung-jun didn't use it…

1275
00:52:52,536 --> 00:52:55,071
-No, not today.
-and Chef Kang-rok.

1276
00:52:55,138 --> 00:52:58,575
Only Chef Jong-won won
after using the perk.

1277
00:52:58,642 --> 00:53:00,243
Then I'll break that record.

1278
00:53:00,310 --> 00:53:02,679
IMMENSE CONFIDENCE

1279
00:53:02,746 --> 00:53:05,048
She returned even stronger.
She leveled up.

1280
00:53:05,115 --> 00:53:06,550
-Her spirit is really high.
-She won't be easy.

1281
00:53:06,616 --> 00:53:08,118
She won't be. She has changed.

1282
00:53:09,052 --> 00:53:11,054
WEBTOON ARTIST KIM POONG'S INGREDIENTS:
SRIRACHA SAUCE, CUMIN, CURRY POWDER

1283
00:53:11,121 --> 00:53:13,123
PICKLES, CHOGOCHUJANG, SEASONING,
JOKBAL, COLA, KETCHUP

1284
00:53:13,190 --> 00:53:15,158
My dish is titled,

1285
00:53:15,225 --> 00:53:17,360
Jok-Ken Goodness.

1286
00:53:17,427 --> 00:53:18,628
Did you just swear?

1287
00:53:18,695 --> 00:53:19,930
Wait, no.

1288
00:53:19,996 --> 00:53:21,164
-What now?
-What now?

1289
00:53:21,231 --> 00:53:22,632
Jok-Ken Goodness.

1290
00:53:22,699 --> 00:53:24,968
-Jok-Ken Goodness?
-Jok-Ken Goodness.

1291
00:53:25,035 --> 00:53:28,004
-What do you mean?
-Jok, like jokbal.

1292
00:53:28,071 --> 00:53:30,373
-What do you think? Take a guess.
-Jok-Ken Goodness.

1293
00:53:30,440 --> 00:53:31,875
Jok from jokbal?

1294
00:53:31,942 --> 00:53:34,044
-Jok from jokbal?
-Jok-Ken Goodness.

1295
00:53:34,110 --> 00:53:35,679
-Is it Jok from jokbal?
-You're right.

1296
00:53:35,745 --> 00:53:37,781
-You're using jokbal?
-I will use jokbal.

1297
00:53:37,847 --> 00:53:38,982
What about "Ken"?

1298
00:53:39,049 --> 00:53:40,183
-Chicken?
-It's Ken from chicken.

1299
00:53:40,250 --> 00:53:42,786
-I see. Jok-Ken.
-Will you use fried chicken too?

1300
00:53:42,852 --> 00:53:44,821
It sounds too heavy.

1301
00:53:45,722 --> 00:53:46,756
SPEECHLESS

1302
00:53:46,823 --> 00:53:48,191
Already?

1303
00:53:48,258 --> 00:53:49,960
-He just shared it.
-It sounds too heavy.

1304
00:53:50,026 --> 00:53:51,561
I'm trying to lose weight, Poong.

1305
00:53:52,262 --> 00:53:53,530
HEAR ME OUT FIRST

1306
00:53:53,597 --> 00:53:55,232
I'll make fried chicken

1307
00:53:55,298 --> 00:53:56,499
with jokbal.

1308
00:53:56,566 --> 00:53:57,867
-What?
-Fried chicken?

1309
00:53:57,934 --> 00:54:00,637
You'll make fried chicken
with the leftover jokbal?

1310
00:54:00,704 --> 00:54:02,405
-Fried chicken with jokbal?
-With jokbal.

1311
00:54:02,472 --> 00:54:05,008
I'll make it half with sauce
and half original.

1312
00:54:05,942 --> 00:54:07,911
CHEF JUNG JI-SUN'S INGREDIENTS:

1313
00:54:07,978 --> 00:54:10,013
MACADAMIA ICE CREAM, GRILLING CHEESE,
GARLIC-FLAVORED CHICKEN BREAST, TTEOKBOKKI

1314
00:54:10,080 --> 00:54:12,749
I prepared Spicy Tteokbokki Gimbap.

1315
00:54:13,316 --> 00:54:16,486
-Spicy Tteokbokki Gimbap?
-Spicy Tteokbokki Gimbap.

1316
00:54:16,553 --> 00:54:20,457
You always end up having leftovers
when you order that spicy tteokbokki.

1317
00:54:20,523 --> 00:54:22,726
I'll try to use that
and turn it into gimbap.

1318
00:54:22,792 --> 00:54:24,594
-Gimbap?
-I see.

1319
00:54:24,661 --> 00:54:26,796
You'll make gimbap by using tteokbokki?

1320
00:54:26,863 --> 00:54:28,732
But only I can make this one.

1321
00:54:30,533 --> 00:54:31,601
Listen to her confidence.

1322
00:54:31,668 --> 00:54:32,802
Only she can make this.

1323
00:54:32,869 --> 00:54:34,004
-That's amazing.
-Wait.

1324
00:54:34,070 --> 00:54:36,039
Did you find the ingredients
to make gimbap?

1325
00:54:36,106 --> 00:54:38,575
I'll grind the tteokbokki
and make jeon with it.

1326
00:54:38,642 --> 00:54:40,377
Then I'll roll it up
with other ingredients.

1327
00:54:40,443 --> 00:54:42,812
-She'll grind the tteokbokki.
-Without laver?

1328
00:54:42,879 --> 00:54:44,514
I'm trying to imagine it, but it's hard.

1329
00:54:44,581 --> 00:54:46,850
-It's hard to imagine.
-It is.

1330
00:54:46,916 --> 00:54:48,018
-Right.
-I'm curious.

1331
00:54:48,084 --> 00:54:50,954
Then let us begin the round

1332
00:54:51,021 --> 00:54:54,324
for Eun-ji's order,
"Satisfying leftover delivery food."

1333
00:54:54,391 --> 00:54:57,627
She's here to show
the class of the original pupil.

1334
00:54:57,694 --> 00:55:00,163
The White Spoon
among Chef Yeon-bok's pupils,

1335
00:55:00,230 --> 00:55:02,832
Chef Jung Ji-sun.

1336
00:55:02,899 --> 00:55:05,835
He's here to show
the madness of the knockoff pupil.

1337
00:55:05,902 --> 00:55:08,972
The Cook of the Darkness
among Chef Yeon-bok's pupils,

1338
00:55:09,039 --> 00:55:11,341
-Webtoon Artist Kim Poong.
-"Darkness"?

1339
00:55:11,408 --> 00:55:15,645
Who'll rise as the true pupil
for Chef Lee Yeon-bok?

1340
00:55:15,712 --> 00:55:18,181
-Let us begin…
-Yes? Like this?

1341
00:55:18,248 --> 00:55:21,451
the 15-minute cook-off!

1342
00:55:22,085 --> 00:55:24,287
An order
for satisfying leftover delivery food.

1343
00:55:26,489 --> 00:55:27,791
EMBARRASSED

1344
00:55:27,857 --> 00:55:28,858
Thank you.

1345
00:55:28,925 --> 00:55:30,093
You sound exactly the same.

1346
00:55:30,160 --> 00:55:32,028
An order
for satisfying leftover delivery food.

1347
00:55:32,095 --> 00:55:33,930
THE ROUND BEGINS FOR
SATISFYING LEFTOVER DELIVERY FOOD

1348
00:55:35,198 --> 00:55:38,068
-The order is in.
-She's using tteokbokki?

1349
00:55:38,134 --> 00:55:41,237
-She'll grind everything.
-Will it, though?

1350
00:55:41,304 --> 00:55:42,706
She's adding water.

1351
00:55:42,772 --> 00:55:45,742
She's adding water. She'll need some.

1352
00:55:45,809 --> 00:55:48,845
-She's adding more red pepper powder.
-She added more red pepper powder.

1353
00:55:48,912 --> 00:55:50,313
That's a lot.

1354
00:55:50,380 --> 00:55:54,417
This situation is enough
to make Won-young faint.

1355
00:55:54,484 --> 00:55:57,954
That's pretty much
like a fiery pit for Won-young.

1356
00:55:58,021 --> 00:55:59,356
It reminds me of the black hole.

1357
00:55:59,422 --> 00:56:00,890
I also feel like I'll get sucked in.

1358
00:56:00,957 --> 00:56:02,158
She ground everything.

1359
00:56:02,225 --> 00:56:03,493
That tteokbokki is extra spicy.

1360
00:56:03,560 --> 00:56:04,828
-It is. Very spicy.
-Yes.

1361
00:56:04,894 --> 00:56:07,030
-I can't take a bite of that.
-It's really spicy.

1362
00:56:08,431 --> 00:56:11,334
-I knew it.
-She's adding more flour.

1363
00:56:11,401 --> 00:56:14,537
Most chefs prepare the ingredients first.

1364
00:56:16,773 --> 00:56:18,408
THE FLOUR REMAINS ON TOP?

1365
00:56:18,475 --> 00:56:21,678
-Chef Ji-sun, it won't get ground up.
-It won't.

1366
00:56:21,745 --> 00:56:24,247
-The flour sits on top.
-It won't ground up.

1367
00:56:24,314 --> 00:56:26,416
She should stir it.

1368
00:56:26,483 --> 00:56:28,785
The more it grinds,

1369
00:56:28,852 --> 00:56:32,222
-the rice cake makes it thicker.
-I see.

1370
00:56:32,288 --> 00:56:34,524
-Why don't you take a spoon…
-It's spinning now.

1371
00:56:34,591 --> 00:56:35,859
It's spinning.

1372
00:56:35,925 --> 00:56:37,694
-It's spinning.
-When we make buckwheat crepe,

1373
00:56:37,761 --> 00:56:39,796
the batter is almost thin
that it runs, right?

1374
00:56:39,863 --> 00:56:42,999
It has to be that thin to make jeon.

1375
00:56:43,066 --> 00:56:44,901
-I see.
-Otherwise, it'll get thick.

1376
00:56:44,968 --> 00:56:47,470
-But that looks thick.
-It does look thick.

1377
00:56:48,805 --> 00:56:50,106
KIM POONG'S FIRST INGREDIENT,
PICKLES

1378
00:56:50,173 --> 00:56:52,742
Pickles. This is the first time
it's opened after I bought it.

1379
00:56:52,809 --> 00:56:55,178
He's using pickle juice.

1380
00:56:55,245 --> 00:56:59,449
Pickle juice has
all kinds of spice and sweets.

1381
00:56:59,516 --> 00:57:01,317
He might make chicken sauce with that.

1382
00:57:01,384 --> 00:57:05,155
Poong, I don't really like pickle juice.

1383
00:57:05,221 --> 00:57:06,256
Oh, my.

1384
00:57:06,322 --> 00:57:07,323
Come on.

1385
00:57:07,891 --> 00:57:08,892
You don't like pickles?

1386
00:57:08,958 --> 00:57:10,627
I don't like the juice.

1387
00:57:11,594 --> 00:57:13,563
Wait, salt. Where's salt?

1388
00:57:13,630 --> 00:57:15,565
He'll season it again.

1389
00:57:15,632 --> 00:57:17,600
-He will, right?
-It'll taste different.

1390
00:57:17,667 --> 00:57:20,069
Pickle juice is boiling

1391
00:57:20,136 --> 00:57:22,539
inside the pan he got from Chef Sung-jun.

1392
00:57:22,605 --> 00:57:23,706
The pan from Chef Sung-jun.

1393
00:57:23,773 --> 00:57:24,908
Will it bring him victory?

1394
00:57:24,974 --> 00:57:26,342
THE KNIFE FROM CHEF YEON-BOK

1395
00:57:27,477 --> 00:57:30,914
THIS KNIFE FIRST CAME
FROM CHEF YEON-BOK…

1396
00:57:32,348 --> 00:57:33,917
LOTS OF ONION AND CHILI PEPPER

1397
00:57:33,983 --> 00:57:37,287
The onion and chili pepper will
taste delicious like that.

1398
00:57:37,353 --> 00:57:41,324
He added onion and chili pepper
into the pickle juice.

1399
00:57:41,391 --> 00:57:42,926
What will they become?

1400
00:57:42,992 --> 00:57:45,428
They'll become pickles. Onion pickles.

1401
00:57:45,495 --> 00:57:46,996
Onion pickles.

1402
00:57:48,465 --> 00:57:50,433
He was making pickles.

1403
00:57:50,500 --> 00:57:52,569
It's just like
how we eat pickled radish with chicken.

1404
00:57:52,635 --> 00:57:54,871
What's that? Oil?

1405
00:57:56,139 --> 00:57:57,841
It looks pretty thin.

1406
00:57:57,907 --> 00:58:01,945
She just ground up tteokbokki
and made them into jeon.

1407
00:58:02,011 --> 00:58:03,480
It looks like jangtteok.

1408
00:58:06,816 --> 00:58:09,385
-Chef Ji-sun, what are you chopping?
-Chicken breast.

1409
00:58:09,452 --> 00:58:11,588
-Chicken breast.
-Chicken breast.

1410
00:58:11,654 --> 00:58:13,490
That must be one of the ingredients.

1411
00:58:14,190 --> 00:58:16,226
-She's frying them.
-She's frying.

1412
00:58:16,292 --> 00:58:18,661
That must be for the gimbap.

1413
00:58:18,728 --> 00:58:21,130
-Will it be like ham?
-Will it?

1414
00:58:21,197 --> 00:58:22,732
That may be the case.

1415
00:58:22,799 --> 00:58:23,800
As the filling.

1416
00:58:23,867 --> 00:58:26,102
If the tteokbokki jeon is too spicy,

1417
00:58:26,169 --> 00:58:27,837
the chicken breast will make it less so.

1418
00:58:27,904 --> 00:58:28,905
Yes.

1419
00:58:30,440 --> 00:58:32,742
Artist Poong is using flour.

1420
00:58:32,809 --> 00:58:34,878
-It's frying powder.
-Frying powder.

1421
00:58:34,944 --> 00:58:37,413
Yes, it's Jok-Ken,
so he has to fry it like chicken.

1422
00:58:38,681 --> 00:58:40,850
That's the curry powder from my place.

1423
00:58:40,917 --> 00:58:42,552
Curry powder.

1424
00:58:42,619 --> 00:58:43,953
Yes, I had curry powder.

1425
00:58:44,020 --> 00:58:45,388
He's good with curry.

1426
00:58:45,455 --> 00:58:47,056
The smell of curry adds good flavor.

1427
00:58:47,123 --> 00:58:48,892
-What's that?
-Lamb seasoning.

1428
00:58:48,958 --> 00:58:51,728
Lamb seasoning. Yes, I had that at home.

1429
00:58:51,794 --> 00:58:53,963
-It has cumin, right?
-It does.

1430
00:58:54,030 --> 00:58:55,765
It has cumin, so it'll kill odd smells.

1431
00:58:55,832 --> 00:58:59,135
He just added seasoning
like curry and cumin.

1432
00:58:59,202 --> 00:59:02,005
Doesn't it smell like tandoori chicken?

1433
00:59:02,071 --> 00:59:04,073
-Like Indian cuisine.
-It smells like Indian cuisine.

1434
00:59:04,140 --> 00:59:06,543
-I see. Are we going Indian?
-It smells so good.

1435
00:59:06,609 --> 00:59:08,411
LEFT HAND!
RIGHT HAND!

1436
00:59:09,312 --> 00:59:10,313
Look at Artist Poong.

1437
00:59:10,380 --> 00:59:13,116
-He's using both hands.
-Both hands.

1438
00:59:13,182 --> 00:59:14,617
He's using both hands.

1439
00:59:14,684 --> 00:59:15,685
He's using both hands.

1440
00:59:15,752 --> 00:59:16,753
Both hands.

1441
00:59:17,754 --> 00:59:19,188
-He's using both hands.
-It won't get mixed.

1442
00:59:19,255 --> 00:59:21,591
He spins the bowl and rubs the powder.

1443
00:59:21,658 --> 00:59:23,426
It's as if he's DJing.

1444
00:59:23,493 --> 00:59:26,429
SCREAM! JOK-KEN IS FOR DINNER!

1445
00:59:26,496 --> 00:59:29,832
It goes so well with his hairstyle.

1446
00:59:29,899 --> 00:59:34,137
2. MIX FRYING POWDER, SEASONING,
CURRY POWDER, AND CUMIN TO MAKE BATTER

1447
00:59:34,203 --> 00:59:36,706
TRYING NOT TO LAUGH

1448
00:59:41,377 --> 00:59:44,213
-What's that? The white thing.
-What's the white thing?

1449
00:59:44,280 --> 00:59:46,049
-Is that a towel?
-The cheese.

1450
00:59:46,115 --> 00:59:47,283
The grilling cheese.

1451
00:59:47,350 --> 00:59:48,451
Yes, I had grilling cheese.

1452
00:59:48,518 --> 00:59:49,986
-You did?
-Yes.

1453
00:59:50,053 --> 00:59:52,288
-It's cheese.
-You had cheese?

1454
00:59:52,355 --> 00:59:54,324
She did. They are delicious.

1455
00:59:54,390 --> 00:59:57,660
In one of the spicy tteokbokki franchises,
there's a place that sells

1456
00:59:57,727 --> 01:00:01,230
gimbap with a whole stick of cheese.

1457
01:00:03,066 --> 01:00:06,869
Chef Ji-sun finishes frying chicken breast
and scoops them out.

1458
01:00:06,936 --> 01:00:09,606
And in another pan, she's grilling cheese.

1459
01:00:09,672 --> 01:00:11,007
My gosh.

1460
01:00:12,208 --> 01:00:13,443
FINISHES THE ONION IN NO TIME

1461
01:00:13,509 --> 01:00:15,011
She has the leisure to check the time.

1462
01:00:15,078 --> 01:00:16,813
She's really fast.

1463
01:00:16,879 --> 01:00:18,281
That must be the filling.

1464
01:00:18,348 --> 01:00:20,984
Chef Ji-sun is really fast.

1465
01:00:21,050 --> 01:00:23,586
She's no longer who she was before.

1466
01:00:23,653 --> 01:00:25,088
I'M NOT THE OLD JI-SUN ANYMORE

1467
01:00:25,588 --> 01:00:29,092
GIMBAP FILLING 3: FRIED ONION

1468
01:00:29,158 --> 01:00:31,694
Doesn't the jangtteok look too watery?

1469
01:00:31,761 --> 01:00:33,096
I don't think it'll get cooked.

1470
01:00:33,162 --> 01:00:35,331
It has to be thin. What's that?

1471
01:00:35,398 --> 01:00:37,800
Look at that. It won't get cooked.

1472
01:00:39,402 --> 01:00:40,637
Ugh.

1473
01:00:41,204 --> 01:00:43,206
This isn't getting cooked. This is bad.

1474
01:00:43,272 --> 01:00:46,209
-The jangtteok…
-It's not getting cooked.

1475
01:00:46,275 --> 01:00:47,844
It's not how creamy it is.

1476
01:00:47,910 --> 01:00:50,446
I don't think she put in enough flour.

1477
01:00:50,513 --> 01:00:53,082
-It won't stick together.
-it won't.

1478
01:00:53,149 --> 01:00:54,384
Then you can't roll it up.

1479
01:00:54,450 --> 01:00:56,653
-You can't make gimbap.
-Oh, no. What will you do?

1480
01:00:56,719 --> 01:00:59,055
-Oh, no. What will you do?
-Chef Ji-sun is in trouble!

1481
01:00:59,122 --> 01:01:02,191
Cooked rice cake won't get sticky again,

1482
01:01:02,258 --> 01:01:03,693
so she needs more flour.

1483
01:01:03,760 --> 01:01:04,861
She's oiling a new pan.

1484
01:01:04,927 --> 01:01:06,629
What should she do now?

1485
01:01:06,696 --> 01:01:07,730
She has to do it over.

1486
01:01:07,797 --> 01:01:09,165
She has to do it again.

1487
01:01:09,232 --> 01:01:12,702
-She's doing it over.
-Will her first try end here?

1488
01:01:12,769 --> 01:01:15,772
She has 7 minutes and 20 seconds.

1489
01:01:15,838 --> 01:01:17,407
SHE'S DOING IT OVER?

1490
01:01:17,473 --> 01:01:20,576
-She's adding more flour.
-I see.

1491
01:01:20,643 --> 01:01:22,412
-This is hard.
-Chef Ji-sun.

1492
01:01:22,478 --> 01:01:25,081
I thought it'd work

1493
01:01:25,148 --> 01:01:27,250
-because there was rice cake.
-They were cooked.

1494
01:01:27,316 --> 01:01:29,819
But she doesn't seem flustered.

1495
01:01:29,886 --> 01:01:31,921
He's frying the jokbal.

1496
01:01:31,988 --> 01:01:35,191
Poong is flustered
because he's scared of hot oil.

1497
01:01:35,258 --> 01:01:38,127
That cook is scared of oil.

1498
01:01:38,895 --> 01:01:41,230
Wait, what's Poong throwing in?

1499
01:01:41,297 --> 01:01:44,300
I want to cool the oil down once.

1500
01:01:44,367 --> 01:01:45,768
I'm stabilizing it.

1501
01:01:45,835 --> 01:01:47,070
You're stabili-jung-hwan it?

1502
01:01:47,136 --> 01:01:50,173
-He's stabilizing the oil.
-You're stabili-jung-hwan it?

1503
01:01:50,239 --> 01:01:51,274
THEY LOVE IT

1504
01:01:51,340 --> 01:01:54,010
-He's stabili-jung-hwan it.
-He's stabili-jung-hwan it.

1505
01:01:54,510 --> 01:01:56,179
THE OIL IS STABILI-JUNG-HWAN

1506
01:01:56,245 --> 01:01:57,847
-What's with that?
-It's making a mess!

1507
01:01:57,914 --> 01:01:59,849
You're a nuisance to your neighbor!

1508
01:01:59,916 --> 01:02:01,317
WHAT'S HE FRYING?

1509
01:02:01,384 --> 01:02:02,785
-What is that?
-Look at Chef Ji-sun!

1510
01:02:06,856 --> 01:02:08,791
SAVE ME

1511
01:02:08,858 --> 01:02:11,260
HE PULLS SOMETHING OUT
FROM THE ABYSS OF DARKNESS

1512
01:02:11,327 --> 01:02:13,029
What is that?

1513
01:02:13,096 --> 01:02:16,032
What's that? It looks like frog legs.

1514
01:02:17,967 --> 01:02:20,870
FRIED FROGS FROM THE OTHER SIDE?

1515
01:02:23,840 --> 01:02:26,609
WHAT DID HE MAKE?

1516
01:02:26,676 --> 01:02:28,511
They look like frog legs.

1517
01:02:28,578 --> 01:02:31,414
That's not for anyone to eat.
The oil was overly heated.

1518
01:02:31,481 --> 01:02:33,883
He's putting the batter in
to cool it down.

1519
01:02:33,950 --> 01:02:36,285
OUT COMES JOKBAL

1520
01:02:36,352 --> 01:02:39,055
If you think leftover jokbal will smell,

1521
01:02:39,122 --> 01:02:42,425
you can throw in that much spice
and kill the smell.

1522
01:02:42,492 --> 01:02:44,527
-Is that so?
-Yes.

1523
01:02:44,594 --> 01:02:47,263
He's covering jokbal with batter.

1524
01:02:47,330 --> 01:02:49,599
It doesn't look so appetizing.

1525
01:02:49,665 --> 01:02:52,935
When you fry chicken,
you can put more dry powder on it

1526
01:02:53,002 --> 01:02:54,804
after the batter.

1527
01:02:54,871 --> 01:02:56,873
Then it won't clump up

1528
01:02:56,939 --> 01:02:59,942
but become nice and crispy.

1529
01:03:00,009 --> 01:03:01,677
He knew that.

1530
01:03:01,744 --> 01:03:03,312
Is he copying something?

1531
01:03:03,379 --> 01:03:04,380
You have six minutes.

1532
01:03:04,447 --> 01:03:07,283
-The time.
-It's not looking good.

1533
01:03:07,350 --> 01:03:09,719
What about Chef Ji-sun's jeon?

1534
01:03:09,786 --> 01:03:10,987
It still looks…

1535
01:03:11,053 --> 01:03:12,922
I hope it gets cooked.

1536
01:03:13,689 --> 01:03:14,690
It won't stick together.

1537
01:03:14,757 --> 01:03:16,359
It's ruined.

1538
01:03:16,425 --> 01:03:19,328
-It didn't go as she planned.
-What now?

1539
01:03:19,395 --> 01:03:20,930
What will she do now?

1540
01:03:20,997 --> 01:03:22,398
I don't think she'll finish in time.

1541
01:03:22,465 --> 01:03:23,800
It must be so nerve-racking.

1542
01:03:23,866 --> 01:03:25,501
That doesn't seem likely.

1543
01:03:25,568 --> 01:03:26,936
THE FIRE GOES OFF

1544
01:03:27,003 --> 01:03:28,504
She needs more flour.

1545
01:03:28,571 --> 01:03:30,206
Should she add more flour and do it over?

1546
01:03:30,273 --> 01:03:32,008
She can put more frying powder on it.

1547
01:03:32,074 --> 01:03:34,043
It'd be better to sprinkle it on top.

1548
01:03:34,110 --> 01:03:36,245
I MUST SAVE THIS!

1549
01:03:38,981 --> 01:03:40,283
This is hard.

1550
01:03:40,349 --> 01:03:42,051
-Did it burn?
-It ripped.

1551
01:03:42,118 --> 01:03:43,653
-It ripped?
-It ripped?

1552
01:03:43,719 --> 01:03:45,755
-Now, Jung-hwan!
-It's me?

1553
01:03:45,822 --> 01:03:47,690
Please go out to the field.

1554
01:03:47,757 --> 01:03:50,126
-"It's me?"
-All right.

1555
01:03:50,193 --> 01:03:52,228
It'll be fine as long as it gets cooked.

1556
01:03:52,295 --> 01:03:54,630
It got ripped right now.

1557
01:03:55,765 --> 01:03:57,600
This is her biggest crisis.

1558
01:03:57,667 --> 01:03:59,335
Poong may take an easy win.

1559
01:03:59,402 --> 01:04:02,672
-An easy win?
-Poong has a big chance.

1560
01:04:02,738 --> 01:04:05,208
This looks like jjigae, not jeon.

1561
01:04:05,274 --> 01:04:07,643
This looks a little ripped,

1562
01:04:07,710 --> 01:04:10,079
but I'm not sure if it'll work.

1563
01:04:10,146 --> 01:04:12,949
They need to stick together.

1564
01:04:13,015 --> 01:04:14,483
-What will happen?
-It's ripped.

1565
01:04:14,550 --> 01:04:16,485
She puts it on the gimbap mat.

1566
01:04:16,552 --> 01:04:17,753
Do you have any rice paper?

1567
01:04:17,820 --> 01:04:19,789
No idea. I need to try.

1568
01:04:19,856 --> 01:04:22,058
She's telling herself to just try first.

1569
01:04:22,124 --> 01:04:23,860
-She'll try.
-"I need to try."

1570
01:04:23,926 --> 01:04:25,962
She puts it on the mat for now.

1571
01:04:26,028 --> 01:04:27,630
-She's trying.
-She's putting in the fillings.

1572
01:04:27,697 --> 01:04:29,532
I see. Just like that.

1573
01:04:29,599 --> 01:04:30,833
She'll make it like gimbap.

1574
01:04:30,900 --> 01:04:33,336
5. TOP TTEOKBOKKI JEON WITH CHICKEN,
CHEESE, AND ONION TO MAKE SPICY GIMBAP

1575
01:04:33,402 --> 01:04:34,704
I think it'll work.

1576
01:04:36,472 --> 01:04:37,907
Chef Ji-sun, will you have the gimbap?

1577
01:04:37,974 --> 01:04:39,642
-I think so.
-I see.

1578
01:04:39,709 --> 01:04:41,043
JUNG JI-SUN GOES TO THE FREEZER

1579
01:04:41,110 --> 01:04:44,513
She does have it. She rolled it up.

1580
01:04:44,580 --> 01:04:46,249
She'll have to cut it, though.

1581
01:04:46,315 --> 01:04:47,750
-That's ice cream!
-She has ice cream.

1582
01:04:47,817 --> 01:04:49,051
Ice cream?

1583
01:04:49,719 --> 01:04:51,587
-Open it for me.
-Sure, I'll open it.

1584
01:04:52,255 --> 01:04:54,690
She just asked the reporter.

1585
01:04:54,757 --> 01:04:57,860
AND THAT WORKED?

1586
01:04:57,927 --> 01:05:00,997
Yes, I'm good at peeling stuff.

1587
01:05:01,564 --> 01:05:02,565
HISS

1588
01:05:02,632 --> 01:05:04,233
Ketchup.

1589
01:05:04,300 --> 01:05:05,668
He put ketchup into cola.

1590
01:05:05,735 --> 01:05:07,703
-Cola and ketchup?
-And chogochujang?

1591
01:05:07,770 --> 01:05:09,005
Ugh.

1592
01:05:10,273 --> 01:05:11,274
I GOT YOU

1593
01:05:11,340 --> 01:05:12,441
That's the sauce.

1594
01:05:12,508 --> 01:05:14,944
Won-young frowned for the first time.

1595
01:05:15,011 --> 01:05:16,445
This is Poong's strong point.

1596
01:05:16,512 --> 01:05:18,814
You think it'll be bad,
but it's not so bad.

1597
01:05:18,881 --> 01:05:20,216
What's with the ketchup?

1598
01:05:21,284 --> 01:05:22,385
What is this?

1599
01:05:23,085 --> 01:05:24,520
What was that?

1600
01:05:25,388 --> 01:05:26,455
It'll clog her veins.

1601
01:05:26,522 --> 01:05:28,024
-Jung-hwan!
-Yes?

1602
01:05:28,090 --> 01:05:29,625
That cola and ketchup mix.

1603
01:05:29,692 --> 01:05:30,726
-The sauce.
-This?

1604
01:05:30,793 --> 01:05:32,261
-Yes.
-He hasn't even started.

1605
01:05:32,328 --> 01:05:33,930
-Don't try to avoid it.
-He doesn't want to.

1606
01:05:33,996 --> 01:05:36,299
-Jung-hwan!
-Can he return without eating anything?

1607
01:05:36,365 --> 01:05:39,635
We only have
2 minutes and 50 seconds left.

1608
01:05:39,702 --> 01:05:41,103
Should I mix it a little?

1609
01:05:41,170 --> 01:05:42,238
Yes.

1610
01:05:42,305 --> 01:05:44,840
-Mix it.
-Mix it?

1611
01:05:44,907 --> 01:05:46,676
I'm getting told to do many things.

1612
01:05:46,742 --> 01:05:49,946
I wonder how that'll taste.

1613
01:05:50,012 --> 01:05:51,280
It's the Jok-Ken sauce.

1614
01:05:51,347 --> 01:05:53,015
WHAT WILL IT TASTE LIKE?

1615
01:05:53,082 --> 01:05:54,984
-And?
-How is it?

1616
01:05:58,187 --> 01:06:01,257
UGH, ARGH! SAVE ME!

1617
01:06:01,324 --> 01:06:02,325
HAPPY

1618
01:06:02,391 --> 01:06:04,727
WATCH OUT FOR INTERNAL INJURY

1619
01:06:04,794 --> 01:06:07,229
-He put in too much sriracha!
-Too much sriracha!

1620
01:06:07,296 --> 01:06:08,531
Sugar.

1621
01:06:08,597 --> 01:06:09,865
-Soy sauce.
-He stopped him.

1622
01:06:09,932 --> 01:06:11,000
-Soy sauce.
-Soy sauce.

1623
01:06:11,067 --> 01:06:13,035
-Hey, you lunatic!
-Soy sauce?

1624
01:06:13,102 --> 01:06:14,303
He just cussed at him.

1625
01:06:14,370 --> 01:06:16,172
You put in too much sriracha!

1626
01:06:16,238 --> 01:06:18,507
-Water.
-He decides to put in soy sauce.

1627
01:06:18,574 --> 01:06:20,476
You should've only put in half.

1628
01:06:20,543 --> 01:06:22,311
I can't eat that, either.

1629
01:06:22,378 --> 01:06:24,380
Won-young said she couldn't eat that.

1630
01:06:24,447 --> 01:06:25,548
Did you hear me?

1631
01:06:25,614 --> 01:06:26,749
"I can't eat that."

1632
01:06:26,816 --> 01:06:29,952
Gosh, this is killing my neck.

1633
01:06:30,019 --> 01:06:32,254
Hey, look at that.

1634
01:06:32,321 --> 01:06:34,357
It looks really nice.

1635
01:06:34,423 --> 01:06:36,392
NOT THIS GUY

1636
01:06:37,360 --> 01:06:40,796
But the fried jokbal looks good!

1637
01:06:40,863 --> 01:06:43,899
-It looks really good.
-Gosh.

1638
01:06:43,966 --> 01:06:45,801
It looks good.

1639
01:06:45,868 --> 01:06:47,436
It looks delicious.

1640
01:06:47,503 --> 01:06:49,672
4. PUT BATTER ON JOKBAL AND FRY

1641
01:06:49,739 --> 01:06:53,509
TEMPTING VISUAL
IS THIS JOKBAL OR FRIED CHICKEN?

1642
01:06:54,410 --> 01:06:56,012
WHAT ABOUT SPICY TTEOKBOKKI GIMBAP?

1643
01:06:56,078 --> 01:06:57,847
Wait, this is…

1644
01:06:57,913 --> 01:06:59,048
IT MAKES HER SIGH

1645
01:06:59,115 --> 01:07:01,550
THIS IS SOMEHOW MAKING ME CHUCKLE

1646
01:07:01,617 --> 01:07:05,254
It does resemble the shape of gimbap!

1647
01:07:05,321 --> 01:07:09,325
-But the gimbap looks really weak.
-It does?

1648
01:07:09,392 --> 01:07:10,426
It's falling.

1649
01:07:10,493 --> 01:07:13,896
It'd be nicer if it were sturdier.
What if she had some laver?

1650
01:07:13,963 --> 01:07:15,765
No, it's all right.

1651
01:07:15,831 --> 01:07:17,900
You have a minute. Hurry up.

1652
01:07:19,035 --> 01:07:20,636
COOKING SPOON, TASTING SPOON

1653
01:07:22,471 --> 01:07:23,606
-Yes?
-How is it?

1654
01:07:23,672 --> 01:07:25,408
-Did you fix it?
-It's a bit better.

1655
01:07:25,474 --> 01:07:28,010
Now, let me taste this again.

1656
01:07:28,077 --> 01:07:31,414
Will he cuss at him again?
Or will he commend him?

1657
01:07:31,480 --> 01:07:32,481
So?

1658
01:07:32,548 --> 01:07:34,316
It's the Jok-Ken sauce.

1659
01:07:34,383 --> 01:07:35,885
-The sweet taste.
-Tell us.

1660
01:07:35,951 --> 01:07:37,553
It's the Jok-Ken sauce.

1661
01:07:37,620 --> 01:07:39,188
If it doesn't look okay,
you can add ginger.

1662
01:07:39,255 --> 01:07:40,656
-The second taste.
-The second taste.

1663
01:07:40,723 --> 01:07:42,892
You have a minute left. Hurry up.

1664
01:07:42,958 --> 01:07:44,260
JUNG JI-SUN FINISHES
SPICY TTEOKBOKKI GIMBAP

1665
01:07:44,326 --> 01:07:46,262
-She's done.
-Chef Ji-sun is done.

1666
01:07:47,063 --> 01:07:48,697
-It's much milder.
-It is?

1667
01:07:48,764 --> 01:07:51,200
But will this sauce go well

1668
01:07:51,267 --> 01:07:52,368
with his Jok-Ken?

1669
01:07:52,435 --> 01:07:54,570
All right. So not yet?

1670
01:07:54,637 --> 01:07:56,338
He's adding garlic. That might help.

1671
01:07:56,405 --> 01:07:57,940
Chef Ji-sun is done.

1672
01:07:58,007 --> 01:07:59,275
Chef Ji-sun is done.

1673
01:07:59,341 --> 01:08:01,744
-It's now under a minute.
-The plates.

1674
01:08:01,811 --> 01:08:02,978
Wait, where are my plates?

1675
01:08:03,045 --> 01:08:04,046
-Where?
-What do you need?

1676
01:08:04,113 --> 01:08:06,348
-You're losing time!
-The plates.

1677
01:08:06,415 --> 01:08:07,683
-Isn't this it?
-No.

1678
01:08:07,750 --> 01:08:09,018
-It's not?
-He needs plates!

1679
01:08:09,085 --> 01:08:11,921
-I have it here!
-Poong can't find the plates!

1680
01:08:11,987 --> 01:08:15,458
-You have 40 seconds left!
-You need to be careful!

1681
01:08:15,524 --> 01:08:16,592
-You have 40 seconds!
-Oh, no.

1682
01:08:16,659 --> 01:08:17,660
Forty seconds.

1683
01:08:17,726 --> 01:08:19,495
Will he finish this?

1684
01:08:22,031 --> 01:08:23,432
Serve it already.

1685
01:08:24,033 --> 01:08:25,267
I'm done.

1686
01:08:25,334 --> 01:08:27,536
You have 30 seconds. Just pour it in!

1687
01:08:27,603 --> 01:08:30,406
-Just pour it in!
-No, it'll get mixed with the original.

1688
01:08:30,473 --> 01:08:32,208
-No.
-All right!

1689
01:08:32,274 --> 01:08:34,076
You don't need decorations.
Just pour it in!

1690
01:08:34,143 --> 01:08:35,878
-No way.
-It's the flavor.

1691
01:08:35,945 --> 01:08:39,582
-You have 20 seconds!
-He's making half sauce, half original!

1692
01:08:39,648 --> 01:08:41,417
-Half sauce, half original.
-You have the basics down.

1693
01:08:41,484 --> 01:08:42,852
Fifteen seconds!

1694
01:08:42,918 --> 01:08:43,919
Poong!

1695
01:08:43,986 --> 01:08:46,155
-Pickles!
-And ten seconds. Ten!

1696
01:08:46,222 --> 01:08:47,790
-Pickles!
-Nine!

1697
01:08:47,857 --> 01:08:50,159
-Eight! Seven!
-Pickles!

1698
01:08:50,226 --> 01:08:51,861
Six! Five!

1699
01:08:51,927 --> 01:08:53,028
-Darn it. Wait.
-Four!

1700
01:08:53,095 --> 01:08:55,364
-Is that it?
-Three! Two!

1701
01:08:55,431 --> 01:08:56,866
-I can't help it.
-One!

1702
01:08:56,932 --> 01:08:59,335
That's time.

1703
01:08:59,401 --> 01:09:02,138
DELIVERING THE PICKLES IN THE PAN

1704
01:09:02,204 --> 01:09:03,739
-The whole pan.
-Wait, with the pan?

1705
01:09:03,806 --> 01:09:06,642
IT'S NOT LIKE HE'S SERVING
HOT POT NOODLES

1706
01:09:06,709 --> 01:09:08,477
Wait, with the pan?

1707
01:09:10,713 --> 01:09:12,681
Come on, Poong!

1708
01:09:12,748 --> 01:09:16,552
This frying pan was truly cursed!

1709
01:09:16,619 --> 01:09:18,487
He's serving it in the pan.

1710
01:09:19,321 --> 01:09:20,623
He couldn't even serve it.

1711
01:09:22,958 --> 01:09:24,393
And of all the pans,

1712
01:09:24,460 --> 01:09:26,695
it was Chef Sung-jun's pan.

1713
01:09:26,762 --> 01:09:28,731
I didn't even get to taste it.

1714
01:09:28,797 --> 01:09:31,500
-This pan is something.
-It is.

1715
01:09:31,567 --> 01:09:34,670
-I never imagined this would happen.
-The lucky frying pan.

1716
01:09:34,737 --> 01:09:36,739
All right, now.

1717
01:09:36,805 --> 01:09:40,509
We were supposed to decide
which one was Chef Yeon-bok's best pupil.

1718
01:09:40,576 --> 01:09:41,810
Wait, right.

1719
01:09:41,877 --> 01:09:44,413
It must feel complicated
for Chef Yeon-bok.

1720
01:09:44,480 --> 01:09:48,384
We feel bad for making you decide
over this round.

1721
01:09:48,450 --> 01:09:51,020
I'm sorry.

1722
01:09:51,086 --> 01:09:52,154
It's okay.

1723
01:09:52,221 --> 01:09:54,590
What happened to your pupils?

1724
01:09:54,657 --> 01:09:57,459
The gimbap keeps falling.

1725
01:09:57,526 --> 01:10:00,629
-It keeps falling.
-I've seen inside out gimbap,

1726
01:10:00,696 --> 01:10:02,765
but never laying down gimbap.

1727
01:10:02,831 --> 01:10:04,667
-It'll go down soon.
-There's an inside out gimbap.

1728
01:10:04,733 --> 01:10:06,602
-There is.
-That's a laying down gimbap.

1729
01:10:06,669 --> 01:10:09,071
It'll be all on the floor after some time.

1730
01:10:09,138 --> 01:10:10,139
It's really tired.

1731
01:10:10,706 --> 01:10:14,109
GIMBAP MADE WITH GROUND TTEOKBOKKI

1732
01:10:14,176 --> 01:10:18,013
AND ICE CREAM SERVED
WITH BLACK PEPPER AND SESAME OIL

1733
01:10:18,080 --> 01:10:21,684
CHEF JUNG JI-SUN'S
SPICY TTEOKBOKKI GIMBAP

1734
01:10:21,750 --> 01:10:24,086
It may look a little…

1735
01:10:24,153 --> 01:10:29,391
So this was the crazy spicy tteokbokki
I had ordered, right?

1736
01:10:29,458 --> 01:10:30,826
Was that what you planned?

1737
01:10:30,893 --> 01:10:32,228
-Yes.
-I see.

1738
01:10:32,795 --> 01:10:35,331
You said only you could make this,

1739
01:10:35,397 --> 01:10:37,132
so we had high expectations.

1740
01:10:37,199 --> 01:10:39,301
Only I can do that.

1741
01:10:39,368 --> 01:10:41,203
-Please have a bite.
-How does it smell?

1742
01:10:41,270 --> 01:10:45,441
It does have a subtle smell
of that tteokbokki.

1743
01:10:45,507 --> 01:10:46,809
-A subtle smell.
-Yes.

1744
01:10:46,875 --> 01:10:50,446
It'd be surprising if someone told me
this was made with tteokbokki.

1745
01:10:50,512 --> 01:10:52,982
The tteokbokki turned into jeon.

1746
01:10:55,184 --> 01:10:57,186
I think it'll taste good.

1747
01:10:57,253 --> 01:10:59,154
She's definitely smiling.

1748
01:10:59,221 --> 01:11:01,290
Was she dumbfounded?

1749
01:11:01,357 --> 01:11:03,158
-Or was it unexpected?
-Or aghast?

1750
01:11:03,225 --> 01:11:06,528
Why does something feel like
shredded squid?

1751
01:11:06,595 --> 01:11:08,197
It's because I fried chicken breast.

1752
01:11:08,264 --> 01:11:10,299
-The chicken breast.
-Fried chicken breast.

1753
01:11:10,366 --> 01:11:12,101
-There was chicken breast.
-Chicken breast and cheese.

1754
01:11:12,167 --> 01:11:15,070
I began to wonder
if I was eating tteokbokki

1755
01:11:15,137 --> 01:11:17,573
or if this was gimbap.

1756
01:11:17,640 --> 01:11:20,476
It's peculiar yet addictive.

1757
01:11:20,542 --> 01:11:22,444
-Is that so?
-Yes.

1758
01:11:22,511 --> 01:11:23,612
-Try some ice cream.
-Is it good?

1759
01:11:23,679 --> 01:11:25,914
-Try some ice cream.
-The ice cream.

1760
01:11:25,981 --> 01:11:29,018
-Sesame oil ice cream.
-Sesame oil, black pepper, and salt.

1761
01:11:29,084 --> 01:11:31,887
-I wonder what it'll taste like.
-Sesame oil on ice cream?

1762
01:11:31,954 --> 01:11:33,722
I think it'll be delicious.

1763
01:11:36,558 --> 01:11:38,894
AN AUTOMATIC SMILE

1764
01:11:38,961 --> 01:11:40,529
-It's good.
-It's good?

1765
01:11:40,596 --> 01:11:41,864
-When you eat it together?
-That's odd.

1766
01:11:41,930 --> 01:11:43,832
I thought it'd be greasy

1767
01:11:43,899 --> 01:11:46,201
with the sesame oil and all, but no.

1768
01:11:46,268 --> 01:11:47,870
The vanilla tastes much stronger.

1769
01:11:47,936 --> 01:11:51,440
She was stressed out
because it didn't look like jeon.

1770
01:11:51,507 --> 01:11:54,143
It would've been much more delicious

1771
01:11:54,209 --> 01:11:57,880
if the jeon had
a little more texture to it.

1772
01:11:57,946 --> 01:12:00,316
Why didn't it become
a proper piece of jeon?

1773
01:12:00,382 --> 01:12:02,151
I failed to keep the consistency.

1774
01:12:02,217 --> 01:12:03,352
The consistency with the flour?

1775
01:12:03,419 --> 01:12:05,120
<i>There was more fish cake than I expected.</i>

1776
01:12:05,187 --> 01:12:07,356
SHE FAILED TO CHECK
THE AMOUNT OF FISH CAKE

1777
01:12:07,423 --> 01:12:09,725
She left out the fish cake
from her calculation.

1778
01:12:09,792 --> 01:12:13,429
-Yes.
-That was why the thickness wasn't right.

1779
01:12:14,129 --> 01:12:18,200
JOKBAL REBORN INTO FRIED CHICKEN

1780
01:12:19,101 --> 01:12:22,838
AND ONION PICKLE IN A PAN

1781
01:12:23,339 --> 01:12:27,209
WEBTOON ARTIST KIM POONG'S
JOK-KEN GOODNESS

1782
01:12:27,276 --> 01:12:29,778
I can't believe this.

1783
01:12:29,845 --> 01:12:31,180
HAHAHAHAHAHA

1784
01:12:31,246 --> 01:12:32,247
-My gosh.
-My gosh.

1785
01:12:32,314 --> 01:12:34,750
EYES SHUT

1786
01:12:34,817 --> 01:12:37,653
-He had no time, so it's in the pan.
-Oh, no.

1787
01:12:37,720 --> 01:12:40,656
-And it had to be that pan.
-Look at this.

1788
01:12:40,723 --> 01:12:44,993
This frying pan
shouldn't be mistreated like this.

1789
01:12:45,060 --> 01:12:47,996
-Chef Sung-jun won with this pan…
-It took first place.

1790
01:12:48,063 --> 01:12:50,432
-during <i>Culinary Class Wars</i>.
-Right.

1791
01:12:50,499 --> 01:12:53,035
You can leave the pickles just to look at.

1792
01:12:53,102 --> 01:12:55,437
I wonder if the jokbal will
taste like chicken.

1793
01:12:55,504 --> 01:12:57,639
-They do look like wings.
-Don't they?

1794
01:12:57,706 --> 01:13:00,376
-They look like wings.
-Can jokbal become fried chicken?

1795
01:13:00,442 --> 01:13:03,312
You've fried these perfectly.

1796
01:13:03,379 --> 01:13:04,380
THANK YOU

1797
01:13:04,446 --> 01:13:07,049
So this will taste like fried chicken.

1798
01:13:07,116 --> 01:13:08,517
-Jok-Ken.
-Yes.

1799
01:13:09,151 --> 01:13:10,152
What's wrong?

1800
01:13:10,219 --> 01:13:12,287
Does it smell bad?

1801
01:13:12,354 --> 01:13:13,722
It's trouble if it smells bad.

1802
01:13:13,789 --> 01:13:16,191
It smells like tandoori chicken.

1803
01:13:16,258 --> 01:13:17,259
Like Indian cuisine?

1804
01:13:17,326 --> 01:13:20,162
-It smells like Indian curry.
-I see.

1805
01:13:20,229 --> 01:13:22,064
He did use curry.

1806
01:13:22,131 --> 01:13:23,265
She takes a bite.

1807
01:13:23,332 --> 01:13:24,566
CRUNCH

1808
01:13:24,633 --> 01:13:27,236
Jok-Ken Goodness.

1809
01:13:28,103 --> 01:13:29,605
Will it taste good?

1810
01:13:30,205 --> 01:13:31,707
SHE CROSSES HER ARMS AND SMILES

1811
01:13:32,908 --> 01:13:34,543
-So?
-I wonder.

1812
01:13:34,610 --> 01:13:36,678
Is the Jok-Ken good?

1813
01:13:37,413 --> 01:13:38,547
Why is this good?

1814
01:13:38,614 --> 01:13:41,550
-It's good?
-She says so.

1815
01:13:41,617 --> 01:13:42,985
Does it feel like fried chicken?

1816
01:13:43,051 --> 01:13:44,887
It feels like fried boneless chicken.

1817
01:13:44,953 --> 01:13:46,021
-Boneless?
-Yes.

1818
01:13:46,088 --> 01:13:48,290
-It doesn't smell bad at all.
-Not at all?

1819
01:13:48,357 --> 01:13:50,392
She'll take a bite
of the Jok-Ken with sauce.

1820
01:13:50,459 --> 01:13:53,662
Jung-hwan almost fainted
after tasting that sauce.

1821
01:13:53,729 --> 01:13:55,063
I tried to put up with it,

1822
01:13:55,130 --> 01:13:57,166
but it clogged up my neck
the moment it went in.

1823
01:13:57,232 --> 01:13:58,534
It must've been fiery.

1824
01:13:58,600 --> 01:14:00,369
He put in too much sriracha.

1825
01:14:00,436 --> 01:14:04,139
She said she liked spicy food,
so I wanted to make it spicy.

1826
01:14:05,107 --> 01:14:07,276
It does smell like
the fried chicken sauce.

1827
01:14:07,342 --> 01:14:08,977
-It does?
-It smells like it.

1828
01:14:09,044 --> 01:14:11,046
-It smells like it.
-And?

1829
01:14:11,113 --> 01:14:13,615
This one has sauce on it.

1830
01:14:14,550 --> 01:14:16,985
LAUGHING OUT LOUD

1831
01:14:17,052 --> 01:14:18,787
-What's wrong?
-It must be good.

1832
01:14:18,854 --> 01:14:20,222
-What's wrong?
-How is it?

1833
01:14:20,289 --> 01:14:22,024
It's good.

1834
01:14:22,591 --> 01:14:24,059
THE COOK OF THE DARKNESS,
KIM POONG!

1835
01:14:24,126 --> 01:14:26,762
That was such a huge twist.

1836
01:14:26,829 --> 01:14:27,930
How about the batter?

1837
01:14:27,996 --> 01:14:30,065
-It's perfect.
-Is it crunchy?

1838
01:14:30,132 --> 01:14:31,834
When you see jokbal,

1839
01:14:31,900 --> 01:14:36,171
-there's the rind area above the meat.
-The rind.

1840
01:14:36,238 --> 01:14:38,040
I can chew all that too.

1841
01:14:38,106 --> 01:14:41,844
That part doesn't really go
with the batter.

1842
01:14:41,910 --> 01:14:44,446
-He should've cut those.
-Yes.

1843
01:14:44,513 --> 01:14:47,382
-And those. The pickles.
-You should try the pickles.

1844
01:14:47,449 --> 01:14:49,485
Pickles in a pan.

1845
01:14:49,551 --> 01:14:51,253
I don't really want to eat this.

1846
01:14:51,320 --> 01:14:53,789
He ran out of time
and couldn't serve it on a plate.

1847
01:14:53,856 --> 01:14:55,624
I mean, this is…

1848
01:14:57,159 --> 01:14:58,427
SHE TAKES COURAGE

1849
01:14:58,494 --> 01:15:00,462
AND TAKES A BITE OF THE PICKLES

1850
01:15:01,296 --> 01:15:03,732
How is it? Does it go with the fried food?

1851
01:15:04,333 --> 01:15:05,501
Is it not so bad?

1852
01:15:05,567 --> 01:15:08,203
-What's wrong?
-It must be addictive.

1853
01:15:08,270 --> 01:15:12,107
-It must taste good.
-She keeps going back.

1854
01:15:12,174 --> 01:15:13,375
You said you didn't want it.

1855
01:15:13,976 --> 01:15:15,477
-She keeps eating it.
-It must be good.

1856
01:15:16,044 --> 01:15:17,346
LAUGHING

1857
01:15:17,412 --> 01:15:19,348
I told you not to drink earlier.

1858
01:15:19,414 --> 01:15:20,415
SHE'S NOT DRUNK

1859
01:15:20,482 --> 01:15:21,617
Come on.

1860
01:15:21,683 --> 01:15:23,418
What's wrong?

1861
01:15:23,485 --> 01:15:26,588
I never eat the radish
when I eat fried chicken.

1862
01:15:26,655 --> 01:15:27,656
But this is good.

1863
01:15:27,723 --> 01:15:29,558
-Really?
-Was it different from the radish?

1864
01:15:29,625 --> 01:15:30,626
It was.

1865
01:15:30,692 --> 01:15:32,461
It almost tastes like dongchimi.

1866
01:15:32,528 --> 01:15:33,962
-Really?
-I see.

1867
01:15:34,029 --> 01:15:36,565
And I don't even know anymore.
This looks cool.

1868
01:15:37,132 --> 01:15:38,300
IT'S GOOD, SO IT LOOKS COOL

1869
01:15:38,367 --> 01:15:39,368
Because of the taste?

1870
01:15:39,434 --> 01:15:42,871
It looks so cool,
almost worthy of a photo shoot.

1871
01:15:42,938 --> 01:15:45,307
I want to see this
when I go to a restaurant.

1872
01:15:46,508 --> 01:15:49,378
-In the silver frying pan.
-Yes.

1873
01:15:49,444 --> 01:15:54,583
Let's try Chef Ji-sun's
Spicy Tteokbokki Gimbap first.

1874
01:15:55,851 --> 01:15:59,488
She grilled cheese
and fried the chicken breast,

1875
01:15:59,555 --> 01:16:03,392
-which makes it feel like squid.
-It does.

1876
01:16:03,458 --> 01:16:05,994
-It's like magic.
-I like that texture.

1877
01:16:06,061 --> 01:16:07,462
That was impressive.

1878
01:16:07,529 --> 01:16:10,599
Artist Poong's Jok-Ken Goodness.

1879
01:16:11,400 --> 01:16:13,602
-Original.
-The original and with the sauce.

1880
01:16:13,669 --> 01:16:15,704
It does taste like fried chicken.

1881
01:16:16,538 --> 01:16:17,906
I can't believe it.

1882
01:16:17,973 --> 01:16:19,408
You got the sauce.

1883
01:16:19,474 --> 01:16:21,343
It tastes like fried chicken.

1884
01:16:21,410 --> 01:16:24,012
-Chef Kang-rok, how is it?
-It does.

1885
01:16:25,314 --> 01:16:27,049
Whenever I see him,

1886
01:16:27,115 --> 01:16:30,118
it's a wonder that he can make
dishes that have a taste.

1887
01:16:31,887 --> 01:16:32,888
A compliment.

1888
01:16:32,955 --> 01:16:36,158
That's why I don't want to fight him.

1889
01:16:36,224 --> 01:16:38,794
-I see. That's a huge compliment.
-He has that surprise.

1890
01:16:38,860 --> 01:16:41,263
-Because of these aspects.
-He's a variable.

1891
01:16:41,330 --> 01:16:43,832
That's why
he doesn't want to fight Poong.

1892
01:16:43,899 --> 01:16:46,368
When Won-young saw him cook, she said,

1893
01:16:46,969 --> 01:16:48,337
"I won't be able to eat that."

1894
01:16:48,403 --> 01:16:50,205
SHE CAN'T EAT SPICY FOOD

1895
01:16:50,272 --> 01:16:51,607
I'm going to take courage.

1896
01:16:51,673 --> 01:16:53,141
-She needs courage.
-Right.

1897
01:16:53,208 --> 01:16:55,110
She wasn't going to eat it,
but she takes courage.

1898
01:16:55,177 --> 01:16:56,445
HOW DOES JOK-KEN
TASTE WITH SAUCE?

1899
01:16:57,012 --> 01:16:59,047
-Mmm… Hmm?
-Hmm?

1900
01:16:59,114 --> 01:17:02,851
It just tastes like
regular old fried chicken with sauce.

1901
01:17:02,918 --> 01:17:04,453
Yes, it's just the ordinary chicken.

1902
01:17:04,519 --> 01:17:07,055
-It could pass as chicken.
-Yes.

1903
01:17:07,122 --> 01:17:10,726
I was somewhat embarrassed
when I saw the two cook at first,

1904
01:17:10,792 --> 01:17:12,194
but I felt proud after a bite.

1905
01:17:12,761 --> 01:17:14,630
WHAT A RELIEF

1906
01:17:14,696 --> 01:17:16,498
-"They're my pupils."
-Yes.

1907
01:17:16,565 --> 01:17:19,067
-Yes.
-Just before, he said, "I'm sorry."

1908
01:17:19,134 --> 01:17:21,570
-He did.
-Let's not judge a book by its cover.

1909
01:17:21,637 --> 01:17:24,272
It's time to make a decision.

1910
01:17:25,741 --> 01:17:27,709
This is an important round.

1911
01:17:27,776 --> 01:17:29,344
Number one, Kim Poong.

1912
01:17:29,411 --> 01:17:31,146
Number two, Jung Ji-sun.

1913
01:17:31,213 --> 01:17:33,815
-Yes.
-Did you push it?

1914
01:17:33,882 --> 01:17:35,717
She did. Okay.

1915
01:17:35,784 --> 01:17:38,387
Who did Eun-ji choose? Let's take a look.

1916
01:17:38,887 --> 01:17:41,657
Jung Ji-sun recreated the taste of squid.

1917
01:17:41,723 --> 01:17:44,359
Kim Poong recreated the taste of chicken.

1918
01:17:44,426 --> 01:17:48,430
Which side did Eun-ji choose?

1919
01:17:48,497 --> 01:17:51,333
Show us the result!

1920
01:17:51,400 --> 01:17:52,834
Who won?

1921
01:17:52,901 --> 01:17:54,369
JUNG JI-SUN
WIN

1922
01:17:54,436 --> 01:17:56,938
CHEF JUNG JI-SUN'S
SPICY TTEOKBOKKI GIMBAP WINS

1923
01:17:57,005 --> 01:17:59,374
Chef Ji-sun wins!

1924
01:17:59,441 --> 01:18:01,777
Poong loses three rounds in a row.

1925
01:18:01,843 --> 01:18:03,545
That frying pan is cursed.

1926
01:18:03,612 --> 01:18:05,681
Is that frying pan cursed?

1927
01:18:05,747 --> 01:18:09,217
I wanted to make
Chef Ji-sun's dish at home.

1928
01:18:09,284 --> 01:18:12,320
The recipe was much easier,

1929
01:18:12,387 --> 01:18:16,224
so it seemed more doable
for people who live alone.

1930
01:18:16,291 --> 01:18:18,326
Also, the curse of the name tag.

1931
01:18:18,393 --> 01:18:21,997
-The one with a crooked name tag loses.
-It kept happening.

1932
01:18:22,064 --> 01:18:24,232
Only Poong's name tag was crooked.

1933
01:18:25,734 --> 01:18:27,903
This is a bummer for Poong.

1934
01:18:27,969 --> 01:18:29,938
You know,

1935
01:18:30,005 --> 01:18:31,807
it looks totally fine.

1936
01:18:31,873 --> 01:18:36,344
I'll keep this and learn
how to use it more properly

1937
01:18:36,411 --> 01:18:39,614
and try once again next time.

1938
01:18:39,681 --> 01:18:43,618
Then Eun-ji,
please put a star on Chef Ji-sun!

1939
01:18:43,685 --> 01:18:47,589
-All right.
-The last star goes to Chef Ji-sun!

1940
01:18:47,656 --> 01:18:49,357
Congratulations, Chef Ji-sun.

1941
01:18:51,059 --> 01:18:54,529
TWO MEN WITH EXTRAORDINARY CHARISMA
VISIT CHEF & MY FRIDGE

1942
01:18:55,664 --> 01:19:00,235
Please welcome actors with a twist,
Hyun Bong-sik and Son Suk-ku!

1943
01:19:00,302 --> 01:19:02,437
I revere you.

1944
01:19:02,504 --> 01:19:03,605
Chef Edward.

1945
01:19:04,606 --> 01:19:06,575
Thank you.

1946
01:19:06,641 --> 01:19:10,212
-I've become the 15-minute man.
-The 15-minute man.

1947
01:19:10,278 --> 01:19:11,646
You've become the 15-minute man?

1948
01:19:11,713 --> 01:19:13,348
You majored in art?

1949
01:19:13,415 --> 01:19:16,551
School of the Art Institute of Chicago
versus Hongik University.

1950
01:19:16,618 --> 01:19:18,186
Their theme is Edward Lee.

1951
01:19:18,253 --> 01:19:20,522
If I win, do I beat the School
of the Art Institute of Chicago?

1952
01:19:20,589 --> 01:19:21,790
Bong-sik is filming this.

1953
01:19:21,857 --> 01:19:23,792
We finally have

1954
01:19:23,859 --> 01:19:27,662
the return match of the final round
of <i>Culinary Class Wars</i>.

1955
01:19:28,430 --> 01:19:29,698
My only focus is winning.

1956
01:19:29,765 --> 01:19:31,166
Look how fast he goes.

1957
01:19:32,067 --> 01:19:34,002
-Chef Sung-jun, how is it?
-Is it okay?

1958
01:19:34,069 --> 01:19:35,270
It's okay.

1959
01:19:37,339 --> 01:19:39,174
The time is ticking. Hurry up.

1960
01:19:39,241 --> 01:19:41,109
-Is it done?
-Oh, no.

1961
01:19:41,176 --> 01:19:44,212
-It's now burning. He can't help it.
-It's too hot!

1962
01:19:44,279 --> 01:19:46,615
It's too hot!

1963
01:19:49,484 --> 01:19:50,619
I can't calm down.

1964
01:19:50,685 --> 01:19:52,020
This is amazing. I'm serious.

1965
01:20:03,632 --> 01:20:08,637
Subtitle translation by: Eunsook Youn
